在公元前10,000年左右[[全新世|全新世]][[文明|文明]]拉开帷幕时，人类人口就开始数次增长。文明之始与[[末次冰期|末次冰期]]结束、[[冰川|冰川]]消退的时间基本重合。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://muller.lbl.gov/pages/iceagebook/history_of_climate.html|title=A Brief Introduction to the History of Climate|publisher=Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratories|accessdate=2013-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170401185130/http://www.muller.lbl.gov/pages/IceAgeBook/history_of_climate.html|archive-date=2017-04-01|dead-url=yes}}</ref>
据估算，约有100至500万人通过狩猎和觅食为生，到了[[新石器革命|新石器革命]]时，人类活动开始从[[狩猎采集|狩猎采集]]向最初的农业转变。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://msh.councilforeconed.org/documents/978-1-56183-758-8-activity-lesson-03.pdf|title=The Neolithic Agricultural Revolution|page=46|publisher=Council For Economic Education|accessdate=2013-05-22|archive-date=2020-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127014712/https://msh.councilforeconed.org/documents/978-1-56183-758-8-activity-lesson-03.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在公元前8000年左右[[农业|农业]]之初时，世界人口约有500万。<ref name=worldometer>"What was the population of the world in the past?", [http://www.worldometers.info/population/ World-o-meters] {{Wayback|url=http://www.worldometers.info/population/ |date=20110112040330 }}</ref>在随后的几千年中，人口数量持续增长，在公元前1000年左右开始提速，到公元前1年时到达2至3亿人峰值。

在541年至八世纪之间的[[查士丁尼大瘟疫|查士丁尼大瘟疫]]导致欧洲人口减半<ref>{{cite web |url=http://science.nationalgeographic.com/science/health-and-human-body/human-diseases/plague-article.html |title=Plague, Plague Information, Black Death Facts, News, Photos |publisher=National Geographic |accessdate=2008-11-03 |archive-date=2013-06-26 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6HfrvlPBO?url=http://science.nationalgeographic.com/science/health-and-human-body/human-diseases/plague-article.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，公元800年后人口平稳增加。<ref>"''[https://books.google.com/books?id=GyE8Qt-kS1kC&pg=PA46&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false Epidemics and pandemics: their impacts on human history] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GyE8Qt-kS1kC&pg=PA46&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false|date=20200922020815}}''". J. N. Hays (2005). p.46. ISBN 1-85109-658-2</ref>然而，增势又被频繁的[[鼠疫|鼠疫]]打断；特别是十四世纪著名的[[黑死病|黑死病]]。黑死病影响了世界人口，从4.5亿人左右降至1400年的3.5至3.75亿人左右。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.census.gov/ipc/www/worldhis.html |title=Historical Estimates of World Population |publisher=Census.gov |accessdate=2008-11-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110102201303/http://www.census.gov/ipc/www/worldhis.html |archive-date=2011-01-02 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>欧洲人口在1340年超过了7000万；<ref>"[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/195896/history-of-Europe/276190/Demographic-and-agricultural-growth#ref=ref994290 History of Europe – Demographic and agricultural growth] {{Wayback|url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/195896/history-of-Europe/276190/Demographic-and-agricultural-growth#ref=ref994290 |date=20121220154316 }}". Encyclopædia Britannica.</ref>直到200年后才恢复过来。<ref>"[http://www.time.com/time/europe/magazine/2000/0717/peter.html Europe's Black Death is a history lesson in human tragedy – and economic renewal] {{Wayback|url=http://www.time.com/time/europe/magazine/2000/0717/peter.html |date=20000815072404 }}". TIME Europe. 17 July 2000, VOL. 156 NO. 3</ref>英国人口在1500年约为260万，在1650年达到560万左右。<ref>"[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/195896/history-of-Europe/58335/Demographics#ref=ref310375 History of Europe – Demographics] {{Wayback|url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/195896/history-of-Europe/58335/Demographics#ref=ref310375 |date=20130723052625 }}". Encyclopædia Britannica.</ref>十六世纪，美洲新农作物通过西班牙殖民地传来，推动了人口增长。<ref>"[http://afe.easia.columbia.edu/china/geog/population.htm China's Population: Readings and Maps] {{Wayback|url=http://afe.easia.columbia.edu/china/geog/population.htm |date=20110719173803 }}". Columbia University, East Asian Curriculum Project.</ref>

在世界其它地区，中国人口在1368年[[明朝|明朝]]建立时约为6000万，在1644年朝代结束时接近1.5亿。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://encarta.msn.com/encyclopedia_761580643/ming_dynasty.html |title=Ming Dynasty: Microsoft Encarta Online Encyclopedia 2009 |accessdate=2010-08-15 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090126181206/http://encarta.msn.com/encyclopedia_761580643/ming_dynasty.html |archivedate=2009-01-26 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>"[http://afe.easia.columbia.edu/special/china_1750_demographic.htm Qing China's Internal Crisis: Land Shortage, Famine, Rural Poverty] {{Wayback|url=http://afe.easia.columbia.edu/special/china_1750_demographic.htm |date=20110708082757 }}". Asia for Educators, Columbia University.</ref>1500年，美洲人口约为5000万至1亿。<ref>J. N. Hays (1998). "''[https://books.google.com/books?id=iMHmn9c38QgC&pg=PA72&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false The burdens of disease: epidemics and human response in western history.] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iMHmn9c38QgC&pg=PA72&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false|date=20200803090223}}''". p 72. ISBN 0-8135-2528-4</ref>

世界其它地区的人在与欧洲探险家接触时常常感染恶毒的流行病。考古学家发现[[新大陆|新大陆]]本土美洲人因[[旧大陆|旧大陆]]传来的疾病，如[[天花|天花]]、麻疹、流感等，死了九成。<ref>"[http://www.pbs.org/gunsgermssteel/variables/smallpox.html The Story Of... Smallpox – and other Deadly Eurasian Germs] {{Wayback|url=http://www.pbs.org/gunsgermssteel/variables/smallpox.html |date=20151125165726 }}". Public Broadcasting Service (PBS).</ref>欧洲人将疾病传染给从未接触过这些疾病的本土人，他们并没有对应的免疫。<ref>"[http://www.millersville.edu/~columbus/papers/goodling.html Stacy Goodling, "Effects of European Diseases on the Inhabitants of the New World"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.millersville.edu/~columbus/papers/goodling.html |date=20080510163413 }}"</ref>

在十八世纪[[工业革命|工业革命]]开始时，人口增长率开始提升。在世纪末了，世界人口接近10亿。<ref name=censushistorical>{{cite web|title=International Programs|url=http://www.census.gov/ipc/www/worldhis.html|website=http://www.census.gov|access-date=2017-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110102201303/http://www.census.gov/ipc/www/worldhis.html|archive-date=2011-01-02|dead-url=yes}}</ref>在二十世纪之初，世界人口约为16亿。<ref name=censushistorical/>到1940年，该数字到达23亿。<ref>{{cite web|title=modelling exponential growth|url=http://www.esrl.noaa.gov/gmd/infodata/lesson_plans/Modeling%20Exponential%20Growth.pdf|website=http://www.esrl.noaa.gov/|accessdate=2017-04-14|archive-date=2020-09-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200920145004/https://www.esrl.noaa.gov/gmd/infodata/lesson_plans/Modeling%20Exponential%20Growth.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

