一些数量研究试图估算全球人口承载能力，即世界人口极限。<ref>Cohen, J.E. (1995). ''How many people can the earth support?'' W.W. Norton & Company, New York, NY, USA.</ref>综合69份元研究显示预估数值为77亿人，依目前的技术来看最低和最高估算分别为6.5亿和98亿。结论得出：“最近，对2050年世界人口稳定水平的预测超出了我们世界人口元估算的极限”。<ref name="Van Den BerghRietveld2004">{{cite journal|last1=Van Den Bergh|first1=Jeroen C. J. M.|last2=Rietveld|first2=Piet|title=Reconsidering the Limits to World Population: Meta-analysis and Meta-prediction|journal=BioScience|volume=54|issue=3|year=2004|pages=195|issn=0006-3568|doi=10.1641/0006-3568(2004)054[0195:RTLTWP]2.0.CO;2}}</ref>

人类对星球的全部影响不单单是纯粹的人口数量。生活方式（包括总和财富和资源利用）和污染（包括[[碳足印|碳足印]]）都一样重要。在2008年，《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》称发达国家居民消耗资源的速度是发展中国家的32倍，如石油和金属，而发展中国家人口占人类的绝大多数。<ref name="NYTimes_Diamond">Diamond, Jared: (2008-01-02). [https://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/02/opinion/02diamond.html "What's Your Consumption Factor?"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/02/opinion/02diamond.html |date=20161226011223 }} ''[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]''</ref>

人口过多和过度消费会影响一些问题或导致问题恶化：
* 清洁水源不足，<ref name = "Shiklomanov-11-32"/>难以供给[[饮用水|饮用水]]、[[污水处理|污水处理]]或排污。一些国家，如[[沙特阿拉伯|沙特阿拉伯]]，使用昂贵的[[海水淡化|海水淡化]]来解决供水不足。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ejpress.org/article/4873 |title=French-run water plant launched in Israel |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091213050101/http://www.ejpress.org/article/4873 |archivedate=2009-12-13 |accessdate=2017-04-17 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.edie.net/news/news_story.asp?id=11402&channel=0 |title=Black & Veatch-Designed Desalination Plant Wins Global Water Distinction |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100324144203/http://www.edie.net/news/news_story.asp?id=11402&channel=0 |archivedate=2010-03-24 |accessdate=2017-04-17 }}</ref>
* 自然资源枯竭，特别是[[化石燃料|化石燃料]]。<ref>Hubbert, M.K. ''Techniques of Prediction as Applied to Production of Oil and Gas'', US Department of Commerce, NBS Special Publication 631, May 1982</ref>
* 增加[[空气污染|空气污染]]、[[水污染|水污染]]、[[土地污染|土地污染]]和[[噪音污染|噪音污染]]。当国家实现工业化并致富时，即便人口继续增长，一系列政府管控措施和技术创新会使得污染大幅降低。<ref name = "opinionjournal-Box">{{cite web |url=http://www.opinionjournal.com/columnists/pdupont/?id=110008416 |title=The Wall Street Journal Online – Outside the Box |publisher=Opinionjournal.com |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2009-12-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091219130145/http://www.opinionjournal.com/columnists/pdupont/?id=110008416 |dead-url=no }}</ref>
* 滥砍滥伐和生态系统破坏<ref name="wilson">Wilson, E.O. (2002). ''The Future of Life'', Vintage ISBN 0-679-76811-4</ref>使得全球大气氧气和二氧化碳水平失衡；每年约有800万公顷森林被砍伐。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mongabay.com/deforestation.htm |title=Worldwide Deforestation Rates |accessdate=2017-04-17 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303205045/http://www.mongabay.com/deforestation.htm |dead-url=yes }}</ref>
* 改变大气成分导致[[全球变暖|全球变暖]]。<ref>''International Energy Outlook 2000'', Energy Information Administration, Office of Integrated Analysis and Forecasting, [[U.S._Department_of_Energy|U.S. Department of Energy]], Washington, D.C. (2000)</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pwc.com/extweb/pwcpublications.nsf/docid/dfb54c8aad6742db852571f5006dd532 |title=The world in 2050:Impact of global growth on carbon emissions |publisher=Pwc.com |date=2006-10-30 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2009-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090109154801/http://www.pwc.com./extweb/pwcpublications.nsf/docid/DFB54C8AAD6742DB852571F5006DD532 |dead-url=no }}</ref>
* [[耕地|耕地]]荒废，[[沙漠化|沙漠化]]逼近。<ref>UNEP, ''Global Environmental Outlook 2000'', Earthscan Publications, London, UK (1999)</ref>滥砍滥伐和沙漠化可以通过采取财产权手段逆转，即便人口继续增长，这种政策依然有效。<ref>{{cite web |last=Polgreen |first=Lydia |url=http://www.iht.com/articles/2007/02/11/news/niger.php |title=Trees and crops reclaim desert in Niger |work=International Herald Tribune |date=2007-02-11 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2007-02-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070213013850/http://www.iht.com/articles/2007/02/11/news/niger.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>
* [[轮耕|轮耕]]有时会采用[[刀耕火耨|刀耕火耨]]，特别在农民人口激增的国家尤是，导致热带雨林栖息地减少，诱发[[全新世灭绝事件|大规模物种灭绝]]及[[生物多样性|生物多样性]]衰退<ref>Leakey, Richard and Roger Lewin, 1996, ''The Sixth Extinction : Patterns of Life and the Future of Humankind'', Anchor, ISBN 0-385-46809-1</ref><ref>[https://news.vice.com/article/humans-are-causing-the-sixth-mass-extinction-in-the-earths-history-says-study Humans Are Causing the Sixth Mass Extinction in the Earth's History, Says Study] {{Wayback|url=https://news.vice.com/article/humans-are-causing-the-sixth-mass-extinction-in-the-earths-history-says-study |date=20180626164339 }}. ''[[Vice_(magazine)|Vice]].'' June 23, 2015. See also: {{cite journal| last1 = Ceballos| first1 = Gerardo| last2 = Ehrlich| first2 = Paul R.| last3 = Barnosky| first3 = Anthony D.| last4 = García| first4 = Andrés| last5 = Pringle| first5 = Robert M.| last6 = Palmer| first6 = Todd M.| year = 2015| title = Accelerated modern human–induced species losses: Entering the sixth mass extinction| journal = [[Science_Advances|Science Advances]]| volume = 1| issue = 5| page = e1400253| url = http://advances.sciencemag.org/content/1/5/e1400253.full| doi = 10.1126/sciadv.1400253| pmid = | pmc = | access-date = 2017-04-17| archive-date = 2017-01-27| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170127233639/http://advances.sciencemag.org/content/1/5/e1400253.full| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Human Population Growth and Extinction|publisher=Center for Biological Diversity|url=http://www.biologicaldiversity.org/campaigns/overpopulation/extinction/index.html|accessdate=2017-04-17|archive-date=2013-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110182056/http://www.biologicaldiversity.org/campaigns/overpopulation/extinction/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Pimm |first1=S. L. |last2=Jenkins |first2=C. N. |last3=Abell |first3=R. |last4=Brooks |first4=T. M. |last5=Gittleman |first5=J. L. |last6=Joppa |first6=L. N. |last7=Raven |first7=P. H. |last8=Roberts |first8=C. M. |last9=Sexton |first9=J. O. |date=2014-05-30 |title=The biodiversity of species and their rates of extinction, distribution, and protection |url=http://static.squarespace.com/static/51b078a6e4b0e8d244dd9620/t/538797c3e4b07a163543ea0f/1401395139381/Pimm+et+al.+2014.pdf |journal=[[Science_(journal)|Science]] |volume=344 |issue=6187 |pages= |doi=10.1126/science.1246752 |access-date=2016-12-15 |quote=The overarching driver of species extinction is human population growth and increasing per capita consumption. |archive-date=2020-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200107225045/http://static.squarespace.com/static/51b078a6e4b0e8d244dd9620/t/538797c3e4b07a163543ea0f/1401395139381/Pimm+et+al.+2014.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>；目前[[灭绝|灭绝]]速度可能高达每年减少140,000个[[物种|物种]]。<ref name="Pimm">{{cite journal | last1 = Pimm | first1 = Stuart L. | last2 = Russell| first2 =Gareth J.  | last3 = Gittleman| first3= John L.  | last4 = Brooks| first4 =Thomas M.  |  year = 1995 | title = The Future of Biodiversity |  journal = [[Science_(journal)|Science]] | volume = 269| issue = 5222 | pages =347–350 | doi = 10.1126/science.269.5222.347| pmid= | pmc=}}</ref>2011年2月，[[国际自然保护联盟濒危物种红色名录|国际自然保护联盟濒危物种红色名录]]列举了总计801个动物物种在人类历史上绝迹，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/2008RL_stats_table_3a_v1223294385.pdf |title=IUCN Red List |accessdate=2009-09-30 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090306194130/http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/2008RL_stats_table_3a_v1223294385.pdf |archivedate=2009-03-06 |dead-url=no }}</ref>但绝大多数灭绝得不到记录。<ref name="Pimm"/>若非人类干预，生物多样性会持续以指数增加。<ref>{{cite journal |author=Sahney, S., Benton, M.J. and Ferry, P.A. |year=2010 |title=Links between global taxonomic diversity, ecological diversity and the expansion of vertebrates on land |journal=[[Biology_Letters|Biology Letters]] |doi=10.1098/rsbl.2009.1024 |volume=6 |pages=544–547 |format=PDF |issue=4 |pmid=20106856 |pmc=2936204}}</ref>大卫·金爵士<ref>Sir David King</ref>是不列颠政府前首席科学顾问，他在议会发言：“不言而喻，二十世纪人口暴增对生物多样性影响超过了所有其它因素。”<ref>"[https://www.theguardian.com/society/2007/jul/11/comment.climatechange Citizens arrest] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2007/jul/11/comment.climatechange |date=20160927193654 }}". The Guardian. July 11, 2007.</ref><ref>"[http://www.scientificamerican.com/article.cfm?id=sixth-extinction Population Bomb Author's Fix For Next Extinction: Educate Women] {{Wayback|url=http://www.scientificamerican.com/article.cfm?id=sixth-extinction |date=20131110212314 }}". ''Scientific American''. August 12, 2008.</ref>斯坦福的欧利希<ref>Ehrlich</ref>称人口增长是地球上灭绝危机的主要致因。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/12/12/world/sutter-vanishing-help/|title=How to stop the sixth mass extinction|first=John D.|last=Sutter|date=2016-12-12|work=CNN|accessdate=2016-12-19|archive-date=2019-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513195544/https://www.cnn.com/2016/12/12/world/sutter-vanishing-help/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

{{quote box|align=right|width=25em|quote=[[白鱀豚|白鱀豚]]、[[灰鲸|灰鲸]]、[[西部黑犀|西部黑犀]]、梅里安姆驼鹿、加州灰熊、[[银红点鲑|银红点鲑]]、大眼鲈和[[海滨灰雀|海滨灰雀]]都是人口过多的牺牲品。|source=—克里斯·赫奇斯，2009年<ref>[http://www.truthdig.com/report/item/20090309_we_are_breeding_ourselves_to_extinction We Are Breeding Ourselves to Extinction] {{Wayback|url=http://www.truthdig.com/report/item/20090309_we_are_breeding_ourselves_to_extinction |date=20170708133758 }}. [[Chris_Hedges|Chris Hedges]] for [[Truthdig|Truthdig]]. March 8, 2009</ref>}}

{{quote box|align=right|width=25em|quote=富裕的西方国家正在以前所未有的速度抽干星球的资源，破坏生态系统。为了给手机找到更多稀土，就想建条横跨塞伦盖蒂平原的高速公路。从海里捕鱼、破坏珊瑚礁、向大气排放二氧化碳。我们触发了大规模物种灭绝 ... 世界人口若为十亿就都会好过。这能过数千年，从长远角度看能维持更多人口，相对而言目前增长失控，未来崩溃会忽然到来 ... 如果每人都以美国水平消耗自然资源 —— 这是世界渴望的 —— 得再来四五个地球。我们正在破坏地球的[[生态系统服务|生态系统服务]]。|source=—[[保罗·R·埃利希|保罗·R·埃利希]]，2017年<ref>McKie, Robin. [https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2017/feb/25/half-all-species-extinct-end-century-vatican-conference Biologists say half of all species could be extinct by end of century] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2017/feb/25/half-all-species-extinct-end-century-vatican-conference |date=20200115005708 }} (February 2017), ''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]''</ref>}}

* 高婴儿和儿童死亡率。<ref>U.S. National Research Council, Commission on the Science of Climate Change, Washington, D.C. (2001)</ref>高婴儿死亡率与贫困有关。富裕国家人口密度大但婴儿死亡率低。<ref>[[:Image:Infant_mortality_vs.jpg|:Image:Infant mortality vs.jpg]]</ref>
* 新流行病和[[瘟疫|瘟疫]]出现。人类受到[[抗生素抗药性|抗生素抗药性]]疾病制约，新病毒感染人类。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/EID/vol11no12/05-0997.htm |title="Emerging Infectious Diseases" by Mark E.J. Woolhouse and Sonya Gowtage-Sequeria |publisher=Cdc.gov |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100306183027/http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/EID/vol11no12/05-0997.htm |archive-date=2010-03-06 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>由于许多环境和社会因素，包括过度拥挤的生存环境、[[营养不良|营养不良]]、缺医少药，穷人更容易受到[[感染|感染]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.who.int/infectious-disease-report/pages/ch2text.html |title=WHO Infectious Diseases Report |publisher=Who.int |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111120042655/http://www.who.int/infectious-disease-report/pages/ch2text.html |archivedate=2011-11-20 }}</ref>
* [[饿死|饥荒]]、[[营养不良|营养不良]]<ref name = "FAO-Italy"/>或与之相关的疾病（如[[佝偻病|佝偻病]]）。不过，富裕国家虽然人口密度大但不至于这样。<ref name=w1/>
* 一些地区贫穷伴随通货膨胀导致集资不多，并伴随暴政。但许多人口密度高的国家已经消除了绝对贫困，降低通货膨胀。<ref name = "heritage-Index-Economic">{{cite web |last=Sherk |first=James |url=http://www.heritage.org/research/features/index/countries.cfm |title=Index of Economic Freedom |publisher=Heritage.org |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2008-02-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080213211732/http://www.heritage.org/research/features/index/countries.cfm |dead-url=no }}</ref>
* 一些国家人口激增时[[预期寿命|预期寿命]]反而降低。<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = McGranahan | first1 = G. | last2 = Lewin | first2 = S. | last3 = Fransen | first3 = T. | last4 = Hunt | first4 = C. | last5 = Kjellén | first5 = M. |title=News and notes: Environmental change and human health in countries of Africa, the Caribbean and the Pacific| last6 = Pretty | first6 = J. | last7 = Stephens | first7 = C. | last8 = Virgin | first8 = I. | journal = Global Change and Human Health | volume = 1 | pages = 9 | year = 2000 | doi = 10.1023/A:1011567429284 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref>
* 由于水资源枯竭，排污系统不佳导致生活环境污秽不堪<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dbc.uci.edu/~sustain/suscoasts/krismin.html |title=Wastewater Pollution in China |publisher=Dbc.uci.edu |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120729121757/http://www.dbc.uci.edu/~sustain/suscoasts/krismin.html |archivedate=2012-07-29 }}</ref>。当然，这些问题可以通过安装下水道解决。如巴基斯坦[[卡拉奇|卡拉奇]]安装下水道后，婴儿死亡率大幅度降低。<ref>{{cite web|title=Clean water could save millions of lives|url=http://the-spark.net/np787404.html|accessdate=2014-07-09|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131226113331/http://the-spark.net/np787404.html|archivedate=2013年12月26日}}</ref>
* 由于没有出路导致贩毒和偷窃等犯罪活动增加。<ref>American Council for the United Nations University (2002)</ref>
* 因资源稀缺和过度拥挤导致冲突，诱发战乱。<ref>Heidelberger Institut fur International Konfliktforschung, ''Konfliktbarometer 2003: 12. Jarlickhe Konfliktanalyse'' University of Heidelberg, Germany (2004)</ref>
* 个人自由减少，约束性法律增加。法律规范人与人之间的关系。人口密度越高，彼此摩擦越多，所需法律和约束也就越多。1958年，[[奥尔德斯·赫胥黎|阿道司·赫胥黎]]认为人口过多威胁民主，导致[[极权主义|极权主义]]政府上台。<ref>{{cite web|title=BRAVE NEW WORLD REVISITED: overpopulation|url=http://www.huxley.net/bnw-revisited/index.html#overpop|accessdate=2014-07-09|archive-date=2020-12-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201230131209/https://www.huxley.net/bnw-revisited/index.html#overpop|dead-url=no}}</ref>
* [[戴維·阿滕伯勒|大卫·阿滕伯勒爵士]]称地球人口数量使所有环境问题加倍恶化。<ref>{{cite web|title=People and Planet speech|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?t=536&v=fK0rXRmC4DQ|publisher=[[Royal_Society_of_Arts|Royal Society of Arts]]|ref=at 13mins,30secs into speech|accessdate=2017-04-17|archive-date=2020-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224072709/https://www.youtube.com/watch?t=536&v=fK0rXRmC4DQ|dead-url=no}}</ref>2013年，他称人类是“地球的瘟疫”，需要扼制人口增长。<ref>[http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/earth/earthnews/9815862/Humans-are-plague-on-Earth-Attenborough.html David Attenborough – Humans are plague on Earth] {{Wayback|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/earth/earthnews/9815862/Humans-are-plague-on-Earth-Attenborough.html |date=20161120085247 }}. ''The Telegraph.'' 22 January 2013.</ref>

这些问题中的许多出现在反乌托邦科幻电影《[[超世纪谍杀案|超世纪谍杀案]]》里，另一作品《[[巨变之后|巨变之后]]》描述了人满为患的地球上食物短缺、资源枯竭、贫困肆虐。

一些经济学家，如[[托马斯·索维尔|托马斯·索维尔]]<ref>Sowell, Thomas (1998-02-12). [http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090708044535/http://www.jewishworldreview.com/cols/sowell021298.html%22 Julian Simon, combatant in a 200-year war]. jewishworldreview.com</ref>和沃尔特·威廉姆斯<ref name=w1>Williams, Walter (1999-02-24). [http://www.jewishworldreview.com/cols/williams022499.asp Population control nonsense] {{Wayback|url=http://www.jewishworldreview.com/cols/williams022499.asp |date=20160515032842 }}. jewishworldreview.com</ref>认为第三世界贫困和[[饥荒|饥荒]]部分由于暴政和经济失策导致。大多数生物学家和社会学家认为人口过多严重威胁生活质量。<ref name=wilson/><ref name="Nielsen"/>一些[[深层生态学|深层生态学家]]，如激进思想家、辩论家彭迪·林克拉认为人口过多威胁整个[[生物圈|生物圈]]。<ref>Pentti Linkola, "Can Life Prevail?", Arktos Media, 2nd Revised ed. 2011. pp. 120–121. ISBN 1907166637.</ref>

==资源==
人口過多除了受人口的規模與密度影響，也取決於人口對可用永續資源的比率，以及資源的使用及分配。

在考量相对于某一生态位的人口是否过多时会观察[[饮用水|饮用水]]、清洁空气、食物、居所、温度和其它维持生活所必要的资源。若生活质量也纳入考虑，需要参考额外资源，如医疗卫生、教育、合适的[[污水处理|污水处理]]、[[污染物排放控制技术|排污]]和能源供给等。人口过多导致在基本生活维持上竞争激烈，<ref>"[http://www.scientificamerican.com/article.cfm?id=growing-population-poses-malthusian-dilemma Another Inconvenient Truth: The World's Growing Population Poses a Malthusian Dilemma] {{Wayback|url=http://www.scientificamerican.com/article.cfm?id=growing-population-poses-malthusian-dilemma |date=20131225120645 }}". [[Scientific_American|Scientific American]] (2009-10-02).</ref>导致生活质量下降。<ref name="Nielsen">Ron Nielsen, ''The Little Green Handbook: Seven Trends Shaping the Future of Our Planet'', Picador, New York (2006) ISBN 978-0-312-42581-4</ref>

直接维系人口健康的是供水，这也是最紧张的资源之一。全球约人口75亿，每人理论上喝2升水，那么每天最少要150亿升水来维系健康生活（美国）。气象气候、海拔都导致洁净的饮用水分配不均。没有清洁水源，健康生活无从谈起。除了饮用，水也用于卫生清洁，为生活创造健康居住环境。水也用于洗澡、洗涤、娱乐、浇灌等用途。灌溉是其中最大问题，若无足够水源灌溉农田，农作物就会歉收，导致粮食供应紧张，甚至引发饥荒。在灌溉之外，耕地也是有限的，不能无限开垦。人口增长需要耕地，没有开垦或过度使用耕地都会影响营养供应平衡。另一问题是耕地相对国家和人口的位置和距离（Bashford 240）。能否得食是影响人口供养和增长的重要限制因素。人口增加，耕地却没有开垦，最终会导致严重冲突。全球土地的38%用于农业，并非想要就有。虽然植物每年生产540亿吨碳水化合物，但若人口增至2050年的90亿，这些植物就供不上了（Biello）。食物供给问题是资源承载能力超负荷的主要例子。若强行在田地上种过多的庄稼，会导致土地贫瘠而减产。因此，超过可持续底线剥削资源，只会杀鸡取卵、适得其反。必须给予足够喘息时间来恢复各个供给来满足当代人生的需求。
<ref>Bashford, Alison. "Population, Geopolitics, and International Organizations in the Mid Twentieth Century." Journal of World History 19.3 (2008): 327–347. Humanities Source Database. Web. 9 Nov 2013.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.scientificamerican.com/observations/2012/09/26/will-humanity-face-a-carbohydrate-shortage/?WT_mc_id=SA_DD_20120927|title=Will Humanity Face a Carbohydrate Shortage?|publisher=Scientific American|date=2012-09-26|accessdate=2014-04-29|author=David Biello|archive-date=2013-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203015312/http://blogs.scientificamerican.com/observations/2012/09/26/will-humanity-face-a-carbohydrate-shortage/?WT_mc_id=SA_DD_20120927|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/popclock|title=U.S. and World Population Clock|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=2014-04-29|archive-date=2021-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210202075809/https://www.census.gov/popclock/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[File:Yangzhou_-_industrial_area_west_of_Wenfeng_Temple_-_P1130239.JPG|thumb]]工业区的一个发电站]]

大卫·皮门特尔称：“由于人口增长和维系生命的关键资源失衡，人类必须积极保护农田、淡水、能源和生物资源。需要开发可再生能源。所有地方的人类都必须知晓人口激增破坏地球资源和人类幸福。”<ref>David Pimentel, et al. [http://dieoff.org/page174.htm "Will Limits of the Earth's Resources Control Human Numbers?"] {{Wayback|url=http://dieoff.org/page174.htm |date=20160710200107 }}, Dieoff.org</ref><ref>Lester R. Brown, Gary Gardner, Brian Halweil (September 1998). [http://www.worldwatch.org/system/files/EWP143.pdf Worldwatch Paper #143: Beyond Malthus: Sixteen Dimensions of the Population Problem] {{Wayback|url=http://www.worldwatch.org/system/files/EWP143.pdf|date=20160303181402}}, [[Worldwatch_Institute|Worldwatch Institute]], ISBN 1-878071-45-9</ref>

[[美国地质调查局|美国地质调查局]]也在报告《[https://archive.usgs.gov/archive/sites/www.usgs.gov/newsroom/article.asp-ID=653.html 地球未来：下一世纪科学挑战]{{Wayback|url=https://archive.usgs.gov/archive/sites/www.usgs.gov/newsroom/article.asp-ID=653.html |date=20170420143834 }}》中有所评价。“随着全球人口持续增长... 人们会要地球更多的资源，包括矿物、能源、空地、水、植物及动物资源。”《[[新科学家|新科学家]]》在《地球自然财富审计》中称我们使用的各种产品所需的各种矿物在近期有被挖光的危险。<ref name="usgs.gov">{{cite web |url=http://www.usgs.gov/newsroom/article.asp?ID%3D653#.U8X8t_S1zkw |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-07-16 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304093234/http://www.usgs.gov/newsroom/article.asp?ID=653#.U8X8t_S1zkw |archivedate=2016-03-04 }}</ref>世界上一些地球学家根据所需矿物计算新技术成本以及在发展中国家的应用传播。所有人一致同意地球人口爆炸和生活标准日益提高对矿物需求是前所未有的，提供的也只有地球。<ref name="usgs.gov"/>矿物的稀缺甚至意味着一些技术从长远角度来看不值得追求.... “以目前的技术来看，一些未开采的金属似乎不足以支持地球上所有人享受现代‘发达世界’的生活质量”。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://environment.newscientist.com/channel/earth/mg19426051.200-earths-natural-wealth-an-audit.html |title=Earth's natural wealth: an audit |publisher=Environment.newscientist.com |date=2007-05-23 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2008-05-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080509083023/http://environment.newscientist.com/channel/earth/mg19426051.200-earths-natural-wealth-an-audit.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

另一方面，一些丰收之角研究人员持乐观态度，如朱利安·L·西蒙和[[比约恩·隆伯格|比约恩·隆伯格]]认为有足够资源供未来人口增长。在2010年研究中，他们在《[[独立报|独立报]]》上总结道：“地球不会（也永远不会）养不起人”。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/opinion/commentators/dominic-lawson/dominic-lawson-the-population-timebomb-is-a-myth-2186968.html |title=Dominic Lawson: The population timebomb is a myth The doom-sayers are becoming more fashionable just as experts are coming to the view it has all been one giant false alarm |work=The Independent |location=UK |date=2011-01-18 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2012-04-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120429213009/http://www.independent.co.uk/opinion/commentators/dominic-lawson/dominic-lawson-the-population-timebomb-is-a-myth-2186968.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>一些批评者警戒这个成本高昂：“就未来几十年全球食物增产来说，技术乐观主义者可能不错...[然而]保罗·R和安·H·欧利希所描述的‘将地球变成巨型人类饲养场’的环境成本会很严峻。伴随人口增长的农业大幅度扩张可能导致进一步的[[森林砍伐|森林砍伐]]、物种灭绝、[[土壤侵蚀|土壤侵蚀]]、农药化肥污染等。”<ref>{{cite web |author=Post a Comment |url=http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000F3D47-C6D2-1CEB-93F6809EC5880000&pageNumber=1&catID=2 |title=Misleading Math about the Earth: Scientific American |publisher=Sciam.com |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2007-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070924121353/http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000F3D47-C6D2-1CEB-93F6809EC5880000&pageNumber=1&catID=2 |dead-url=no }}</ref>由于人类与地球生命系统唇齿相连，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nasadaacs.eos.nasa.gov/articles/2005/2005_mea.html |title=NASA Earth Science Data and Services: Checking Earth's Vital Signs |publisher=Nasadaacs.eos.nasa.gov |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111104215208/http://nasadaacs.eos.nasa.gov/articles/2005/2005_mea.html |archivedate=2011-11-04 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.greenfacts.org/en/ecosystems/ |title=Ecosystem Change: Scientific Facts on Ecosystem Change |publisher=Greenfacts.org |date=2011-10-17 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2020-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201105231913/http://www.greenfacts.org/en/ecosystems/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://pubs.usgs.gov/of/2002/of02-349/ |title=USGS OFR 02-349: Human Impact on the Planet: An Earth Science Perspective and Ethical Considerations |publisher=Pubs.usgs.gov |date=2002-10-07 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2020-08-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200808010156/https://pubs.usgs.gov/of/2002/of02-349/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>一些科学家质疑继续扩张是否明智。

《[[千禧年生态系统评估|千禧年生态系统评估]]》是份由1,360位世界著名科学家历经4年的研究成果，旨在度量自然资源对人类和世界的实际价值。据该报告称：“在二十世纪下半叶，世界生态系统结构急剧变化，超过人类历史上任何时期，现在几乎所有地球生态系统都深受人类活动影响。”<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.greenfacts.org/en/ecosystems/millennium-assessment-3/1-ecosystem-change.htm#1p1 |title=1. How have ecosystems changed? |publisher=Greenfacts.org |date=2011-10-17 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2020-06-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200621014105/http://www.greenfacts.org/en/ecosystems/millennium-assessment-3/1-ecosystem-change.htm#1p1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>“生态系统服务，特别是食物生产、木材和渔业，对就业和经济活动来说很重要。高强度使用生态系统常在短期内获得暴利，但从长远看，过度和不可持续的滥用导致亏损。一个国家可以不留青山、竭泽而渔，得到靓丽的GDP，失去固定资产。如果生态系统的全部经济价值被纳入决策，其退化将被扼制甚至逆转。”<ref name = "ecosystems-#3">{{cite web |url=http://www.greenfacts.org/en/ecosystems/#3 |title=Ecosystem Change: Scientific Facts on Ecosystem Change |publisher=Greenfacts.org |date=2011-10-17 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2020-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201105231913/http://www.greenfacts.org/en/ecosystems/#3 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.greenfacts.org/en/ecosystems/millennium-assessment-3/3-human-wellbeing-poverty.htm#2p0 |title=3. How have ecosystem changes affected human well-being and poverty alleviation? |publisher=Greenfacts.org |date=2011-10-17 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2020-11-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201106122614/https://www.greenfacts.org/en/ecosystems/millennium-assessment-3/3-human-wellbeing-poverty.htm#2p0 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[联合国环境署|联合国环境署]]另一项研究为《全球环境展望》<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unep.org/geo/geo4/media/ |title=Global Environmental Outlook – 4 |publisher=Unep.org |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090707144222/http://www.unep.org/geo/geo4/media/ |archivedate=2009-07-07 }}</ref>，由1,400名科学家历经5年完成，得出类似结论。报告“发现人类消费远远超过可用资源。现在，每个人需要地球额外提供三分之一的土地来满足需求。”{{Page needed|date=November 2010}}它将问题归咎于没有“响应或承认每个人或地球环境所面对的挑战之大... ‘系统性毁灭地球自然或基于自然的资源已经挑战了经济可行性 —— 我们交给孩子们的账单可能支付不起...” 报告作者称它的目标“不是给出黑暗和阴郁的剧情，而是紧急呼吁行动。”它警告“应对问题可能会触及强大的既得利益集团，环境问题必须提升到决策中央... ”<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unep.org/geo/geo4/media/ |title=Global Environment Outlook: environment for development (GEO-4) |publisher=Unep.org |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090707144222/http://www.unep.org/geo/geo4/media/ |archivedate=2009-07-07 }}</ref>{{Page needed|date=November 2010}}

虽然所有资源，无论矿藏或其它等，在地球上都是有限的，当某一资源出现稀缺或高需求时都会有一定程度的自我调整。例如，1990年已知自然资源储量不少，虽然需求高消费高，价格相对1970年下降。只要价格钉出现，市场常常自我修正，寻找替代资源或新技术。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.un.org/esa/population/publications/wpm/wpm2001.pdf|format=PDF|title=UN World Population Report 2001|page=34|accessdate=2008-12-16|archive-date=2018-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211183328/http://www.un.org/esa/population/publications/wpm/wpm2001.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 淡水 ===
农业所必须的[[淡水|淡水]]供应在全球范围内每况愈下。<ref>Brown, Lester R. and Halweil, Brian (1999-09-23). [https://web.archive.org/web/20090314104500/http://www.worldwatch.org/node/1661 Population Outrunning Water Supply as World Hits 6 Billion]. Worldwatch Institute.</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Fred Pearce|title=When the Rivers Run Dry: Water—The Defining Crisis of the Twenty-first Century|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=C0_q-90H1aAC|year=2007|publisher=Beacon Press|isbn=978-0-8070-8573-8|access-date=2017-04-19|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109130954/https://books.google.com/books?id=C0_q-90H1aAC|dead-url=no}}</ref>随着人口增加，水源危机会加剧。<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1HEwh8nsljQC&printsec=frontcover&dq=Outgrowing+The+Earth:+The+Food+Security+Challenge+in+an+Age+of+Falling+Water+Tables+and+Rising+Temperature&hl=en&sa=X&ei=cUX9UtGFGJDksATpiYG4Dw&ved=0CCsQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Outgrowing%20The%20Earth%3A%20The%20Food%20Security%20Challenge%20in%20an%20Age%20of%20Falling%20Water%20Tables%20and%20Rising%20Temperature&f=false |last=Worldwatch |first=The |title=Outgrowing the Earth: The Food Security Challenge in an Age of Falling Water Tables and Rising Temperatures: Books: Lester R. Brown |publisher=Amazon.com |isbn=0393060705 |access-date=2017-04-19 |archive-date=2019-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190511110035/https://books.google.com/books?id=1HEwh8nsljQC&printsec=frontcover&dq=Outgrowing+The+Earth:+The+Food+Security+Challenge+in+an+Age+of+Falling+Water+Tables+and+Rising+Temperature&hl=en&sa=X&ei=cUX9UtGFGJDksATpiYG4Dw&ved=0CCsQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Outgrowing%20The%20Earth%3A%20The%20Food%20Security%20Challenge%20in%20an%20Age%20of%20Falling%20Water%20Tables%20and%20Rising%20Temperature&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>

如下是海水淡化的潜在问题，不过，世界绝大多数淡水在极地冰盖上和地下水系统里。

淡水可以从海水淡化得来。例如，[[马耳他|马耳他]]三分之二的淡水来自海水淡化。一些海水淡化厂靠[[核动力|核动力]]驱动。<ref>{{cite web |title=Nuclear Desalination |url=http://www.uic.com.au/nip74.htm |website=https://web.archive.org/ |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070208191547/http://www.uic.com.au/nip74.htm |archivedate=2007-02-08 |accessdate=2017-04-19 }}</ref><ref name="stanford-cohen">{{cite journal |doi=10.1119/1.13440 |url=http://www.sustainablenuclear.org/PADs/pad11983cohen.pdf |title=Breeder reactors: A renewable energy source |author=Cohen, Bernard L. |journal=American Journal of Physics |volume=51 |issue=1 |pages=75–76 |year=1983 |bibcode=1983AmJPh..51...75C |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130114062518/http://sustainablenuclear.org/PADs/pad11983cohen.pdf |archivedate=2013-01-14 |access-date=2017-04-19 }}</ref>不过，海水淡化成本高昂，将大量经过淡化的海水送往全国，特别对于贫穷国家来说不大现实。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thenation.com/doc/20020902/barlow |title=Who Owns Water? |publisher=Thenation.com |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2010-04-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100429154115/http://www.thenation.com/doc/20020902/barlow |dead-url=no }}</ref>海水淡化成本不一；目前以色列淡化成本为每立方米53分钱，<ref name = "ejpress-water"/>新加坡为49分钱，<ref name = "edie-distinct"/>美国为81分钱（合1,000加仑3.06美元）<ref>{{cite web|title=Desalination gets a serious look|url=http://www.lasvegassun.com/news/2008/mar/21/desalination-gets-serious-look/|website=http://www.lasvegassun.com|accessdate=2017-04-19|archive-date=2018-07-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180710180500/https://lasvegassun.com/news/2008/mar/21/desalination-gets-serious-look/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

根据周和托尔2004年的研究，“海水淡化成本等于将水泵上2000米，或远送1600千米。对于远离海洋的高海拔地带，如[[利雅得|利雅得]]和[[哈拉雷|哈拉雷]]，海水淡化很贵。另一些地区，主要成本是淡化而非运输。像北京、[[曼谷|曼谷]]、[[萨拉戈萨|萨拉戈萨]]、[[鳳凰城_(亞利桑那州)|鳳凰城]]，当然像[[的黎波里|的黎波里]]的沿海城市，成本会低些。”因此，研究对于滨海富裕地区应用该技术表示肯定，它总结道：“海水淡化可能是一些水源紧张地区的解决办法，但贫穷的、远在内陆的或高海拔的地区则不然。不幸的是，那些地方最缺水。”<ref name="uni-hamburg.de">{{cite journal|journal=Water Resources Research|volume=41|pages=W03003|year=2005|doi=10.1029/2004WR003749|title=Evaluating the costs of desalination and water transport|author1=Zhou, Yuan  |author2=Tol, Richard S. J.|bibcode=2005WRR....4103003Z|issue=3}}</ref>另一个潜在问题是副产品盐湖卤水，如果在高温时倒回海水，会导致严重海洋污染。<ref name="uni-hamburg.de"/>

世界最大的海水淡化厂位于阿拉伯联合酋长国阿里山港口（Phase 2），每年生产3亿立方米的淡水，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldwater.org/data20062007/Table21.pdf |title=100 Largest Desalination Plants Planned, in Construction, or in Operation—1 January 2005 |format=PDF |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101221231528/http://worldwater.org/data20062007/Table21.pdf |archivedate=2010-12-21 }}</ref>合每秒2500加仑左右。美国最大的海水淡化厂位于佛罗里达州[[坦帕湾|坦帕湾]]，在2007年12月开始每天淡化2500万加仑（95000立方米）的水。2008年1月17日的《华尔街日报》文章称：“根据国际海水淡化协会，全世界海水淡化厂每天生产120多亿加仑的水。”<ref>{{cite web|title=Water, Water, Everywhere|url=https://www.wsj.com/news/articles/SB120053698876396483?mg=reno64-wsj&url=http%3A%2F%2Fonline.wsj.com%2Farticle%2FSB120053698876396483.html%3F|website=http://online.wsj.com|accessdate=2017-04-20|archive-date=2016-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160314085437/http://www.wsj.com/news/articles/SB120053698876396483?mg=reno64-wsj&url=http%3A%2F%2Fonline.wsj.com%2Farticle%2FSB120053698876396483.html%3F|dead-url=no}}</ref>沙特阿拉伯在[[朱拜勒_(沙特阿拉伯)|朱拜勒]]淡化海水后，经管道送水{{convert|200|mi|km}}至内陆首都[[利雅得|利雅得]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Desalination is the Solution to Water Shortages|url=http://www.redorbit.com/news/science/1367352/desalination_is_the_solution_to_water_shortages|website=http://www.redorbit.com/|accessdate=2017-04-20|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112033615/https://www.redorbit.com/news/science/1367352/desalination_is_the_solution_to_water_shortages/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

然而，[[国际原子能机构|国际原子能机构]][[重力回復及氣候實驗衛星|重力回復及氣候實驗衛星]]和同位素实验的新数据显示位于地球最大最干旱地区之下的努比亚含水层有足够水源供“至少几个世纪用”。除此之外，新地图精细地描述了地下水储备，新技术能够相对廉价地泵水出来。<ref>Wald, Chelsea (2012-02-15). [http://www.newscientist.com/article/mg21328512.200-uncharted-waters-probing-aquifers-to-head-off-war.html Uncharted waters: Probing aquifers to head off war] {{Wayback|url=http://www.newscientist.com/article/mg21328512.200-uncharted-waters-probing-aquifers-to-head-off-war.html |date=20150423103654 }}. New Scientist</ref>

===食物===
一些科学家认为维持世界人口的食物不够吃，<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Haynes, Michael  |author2=Husan, Rumy |year= 2000 |title=National inequality and the catch-up period: Some "growth alone" scenarios" |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-economic-issues_2000-09_34_3/page/693  |journal=Journal of Economic Issues|volume=34|issue=3 |quote=In a world that now produces more food than is necessary to feed all its population [UN 1994], there is no excuse for hunger and starvation.|jstor=4227593|pages=693–705}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Gilland | first1 = B. | doi = 10.1016/S0306-9192(02)00002-7 | title = World population and food supply | journal = Food Policy | volume = 27 | pages = 47–38 | year = 2002 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref>此事有争议，特别是在可持续性上。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.globalchange.umich.edu/globalchange2/current/lectures/food_supply/food.htm |title=Human Appropriation of the World's Food Supply |publisher=Globalchange.umich.edu |date=2000-12-15 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111204153025/http://www.globalchange.umich.edu/globalchange2/current/lectures/food_supply/food.htm |archivedate=2011-12-04 }}</ref>

许多国家大量依靠进口。埃及和伊朗的粮食四成靠进口。也门和以色列得进口九成多的粮食。只有6个国家：阿根廷、澳大利亚、加拿大、法国、泰国和美国出口九成粮食。近十年来，美国占世界粮食出口的近一半。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.earth-policy.org/Books/Out/Ote1_5.htm |title=Pushing Beyond the Earth's Limits The Japan Syndrome |publisher=Earth-policy.org |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090708052346/http://www.earth-policy.org/Books/Out/Ote1_5.htm |archivedate=2009-07-08 }}</ref><ref name="The Food Bubble Economy">{{cite web |url=http://www.i-sis.org.uk/TFBE.php |title=The Food Bubble Economy |publisher=I-sis.org.uk |date=2002-04-12 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2016-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160122234915/http://www.i-sis.org.uk/TFBE.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2001年联合国报告称人口增长是“农业需求增加的主要驱动力”，但在假定人口增速放缓情况下，“对全球粮食生产能力能否满足可预见未来的需求（即至2030到2050年左右），专家最新评估持谨慎乐观态度”。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.un.org/esa/population/publications/wpm/wpm2001.pdf|format=PDF|title=UN World Population Report 2001|page=38|accessdate=2008-12-16|archive-date=2018-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211183328/http://www.un.org/esa/population/publications/wpm/wpm2001.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

不过，2007年观察数据显示世界营养不良绝对人数在1995年为8.32亿，对比2007年的9.23亿实际有所增加。<ref>[[Food_and_Agriculture_Organization|Food and Agriculture Organization]] Economic and Social Development Department. [http://www.fao.org/docrep/011/i0291e/i0291e00.htm "The State of Food Insecurity in the World, 2008 : High food prices and food security – threats and opportunities"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.fao.org/docrep/011/i0291e/i0291e00.htm |date=20161026084651 }}. [[FAO|FAO]] of the United Nations, 2008, p. 2.</ref>最近，[[联合国粮食及农业组织|联合国粮食及农业组织]]估算出更急剧的增量，为2009年的10.2亿。<ref>{{cite web|title=1.02 billion people hungry|url=http://www.fao.org/news/story/en/item/20568/icode/|website=http://www.fao.org/|accessdate=2017-04-17|archive-date=2012-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121117211313/http://www.fao.org/news/story/en/item/20568/icode/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

====展望全球====
{{Further information|2007-08年全球粮食价格危机}}
[[File:Food_production_per_capita.svg|thumb]]

这里讨论的自然资源总量并非永恒不变，分布并非[[零和博弈|此消彼长]]。例如，由于[[绿色革命|绿色革命]]及更多耕地开垦，世界食物产量在1995年前稳固增长。2005年，世界人均食物产量显著高于1961年的产量。

当世界人口从30亿增至60亿时，贫穷国家每日[[卡路里|卡路里]]消费从1,932增至2,650，当地营养不良人口比率从45%降至18%。这说明第三世界贫困和饥饿是由于发展欠佳而非人口过多所致。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.economist.com/science/displayStory.cfm?Story_ID=718860 | work=The Economist | title=The truth about the environment | date=2001-08-02 | accessdate=2017-04-22 | archive-date=2010-02-01 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100201080201/http://www.economist.com/science/displayStory.cfm?Story_ID=718860 | dead-url=no }}</ref>然而，其它人质疑这些数据。<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite journal|url=http://www.nicholas.duke.edu/people/faculty/pimm/publications/pimmreprints/170_Pimm_Harvey_Nature.pdf|doi=10.1038/35102629|title=No need to worry about the future|year=2001|last1=Pimm|first1=Stuart|last2=Harvey|first2=Jeff|journal=Nature|volume=414|issue=6860|page=149|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070610083807/http://www.nicholas.duke.edu/people/faculty/pimm/publications/pimmreprints/170_Pimm_Harvey_Nature.pdf|archivedate=2007-06-10|access-date=2017-04-22}}</ref>从1950到1984年，绿色革命改变了世界农业，粮食增产超过250%。<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Kindall, Henery W |author2=Pimentel, David |title=Constraints on the Expansion of the Global Food Supply |journal=Ambio. |volume=23 |issue=3 |date=May 1994 |url=http://dieoff.org/page36.htm |author= |access-date=2017-04-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011060735/http://dieoff.org/page36.htm |archive-date=2018-10-11 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>自绿色革命起，世界人口已经增加40亿左右，大多数人认为，若非绿色革命，饥荒和营养不良会打破联合国现有文献记录。<ref name="The limits of a Green Revolution" /><ref>"[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2008/feb/26/food.unitednations Feed the world? We are fighting a losing battle, UN admits] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2008/feb/26/food.unitednations |date=20161225150554 }}". The Guardian (2008-02-26).</ref>

[[肥胖症|超重人数]]已经超过了营养不良人数。2006年，[[MSNBC|MSNBC]]报道称：“全世界约有8亿人营养不良，超过10亿人超重。”美国是世界上肥胖比率最高的国家之一。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/14407969/ |title=Nearly 1 in 5 Chinese overweight or obese – Diet and nutrition |publisher=MSNBC |date=2006-08-18 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2012-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121105153204/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/14407969/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>
然而，研究显示富裕的、有教育的人吃健康食物更多，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-13/diet/33424074_1_higher-levels-poor-countries-richer-countries |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130126072352/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-09-13/diet/33424074_1_higher-levels-poor-countries-richer-countries |archive-date=2013-01-26 |title= |dead-url=yes |accessdate=2016-06-01 }}</ref>显示肥胖是因贫困、缺乏教育、吃高卡路里和低营养价值的垃圾食物所导致的疾病。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://frac.org/initiatives/hunger-and-obesity/are-low-income-people-at-greater-risk-for-overweight-or-obesity/ |title=Relationship Between Poverty and Overweight or Obesity « Food Research & Action Center |publisher=Frac.org |date= |accessdate=2013-09-22 |archive-date=2016-11-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161128041102/http://frac.org/initiatives/hunger-and-obesity/are-low-income-people-at-greater-risk-for-overweight-or-obesity/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/local/2012/06/13/data-sobering-on-ohio-kids-poverty-obesity.html |title=Data sobering on Ohio kids’ poverty, obesity | The Columbus Dispatch |publisher=Dispatch.com |date=2012-06-13 |accessdate=2013-09-22 |archive-date=2020-08-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809074430/https://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/local/2012/06/13/data-sobering-on-ohio-kids-poverty-obesity.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[File:Percentage_population_undernourished_world_map.PNG|thumb]]

[[联合国粮食及农业组织|联合国粮食及农业组织]]在报告《2006年世界食物危险情况》中称发展中国家营养不良的人数下降了约300万人，从1990至1992年的20%减至17%。组织进一步预期2015年发展中国家饥民比率相比1990至1992年会减半至10%。组织称：我们强调先减少饥饿，这在全球范围来说已经不是方式方法问题了。今天，世界比十年期更加富有。食物更多，并能够进一步增产而不必担心价格上行压力。减少饥饿的知识和资源都有，缺乏的是足够的政治决心来动员这些资源服务饥民。”<ref>[ftp://ftp.fao.org/docrep/fao/009/a0750e/a0750e01.pdf The State of Food Insecurity in the World 2006]{{dead link|date=December 2016|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}. Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (2006) ISBN 92-5-105580-7 ftp.fao.org</ref>

2008年，由于更多农业转而生产[[生物燃料|生物燃料]]，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundayherald.com/news/heraldnews/display.var.2104849.0.2008_the_year_of_global_food_crisis.php |title=2008: The year of global food crisis |publisher=Sundayherald.com |date=2008-03-08 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090822070637/http://www.sundayherald.com/news/heraldnews/display.var.2104849.0.2008_the_year_of_global_food_crisis.php |archivedate=2009-08-22 }}</ref>世界[[油价|油价]]超过每桶100美元，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.csmonitor.com/2008/0118/p08s01-comv.html |title=The global grain bubble |publisher=Csmonitor.com |date=2008-01-18 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2009-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091130063759/http://www.csmonitor.com/2008/0118/p08s01-comv.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>全球人口增长，<ref>{{cite news |author=James Randerson, science correspondent |url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2008/mar/07/scienceofclimatechange.food |title=Food crisis will take hold before climate change, warns chief scientist |work=The Guardian |location=UK |accessdate=2011-11-30 |date=2008-03-07 |archive-date=2013-09-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902035723/http://www.theguardian.com/science/2008/mar/07/scienceofclimatechange.food |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[气候变化|气候变化]]，<ref>{{cite news |author=John Vidal, environment editor |url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2007/nov/03/food.climatechange |title=Global food crisis looms as climate change and fuel shortages bite |work=The Guardian |location=UK |accessdate=2011-11-30 |date=2007-11-03 |archive-date=2013-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130930145154/http://www.theguardian.com/environment/2007/nov/03/food.climatechange |dead-url=no }}</ref>居民和工业用地占用耕地<ref>{{cite web |author=Walsoft |url=http://www.marketoracle.co.uk/Article3782.html |title=Experts: Global Food Shortages Could 'Continue for Decades' |publisher=Marketoracle.co.uk |date=2008-02-22 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2013-02-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130221180143/http://www.marketoracle.co.uk/Article3782.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Moya K. Mason |url=http://www.moyak.com/papers/urbanization-agriculture.html |title=Has Urbanization Caused a Loss to Agricultural Land? |publisher=Moyak.com |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2013-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130924182503/http://www.moyak.com/papers/urbanization-agriculture.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>以及中国和印度消费需求增加<ref>{{cite news |last=Walt |first=Vivienne |url=http://www.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,1717572,00.html |title=The World's Growing Food-Price Crisis |work=Time |date=2008-02-27 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2011-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111129211855/http://www.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,1717572,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/7284196.stm |title=The cost of food: Facts and figures |publisher=BBC News |date=2008-10-16 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2009-01-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090120025945/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/7284196.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>导致粮价攀升，世界许多国家出现了[[2007-08年全球粮食价格危机|食物暴动]]<ref>{{cite news |author=Jonathan Watts in Beijing |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2007/dec/04/china.business |title=Riots and hunger feared as demand for grain sends food costs soaring |work=The Guardian |location=UK |accessdate=2011-11-30 |date=2007-12-04 |archive-date=2013-09-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130901000000/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2007/dec/04/china.business |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Roland Watson and Sam Fleming 30 November 2011 12:01 am |url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/environment/article3500975.ece |title=Already we have riots, hoarding, panic: the sign of things to come? |work=The Times |location=UK |date=2009-06-25 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2011-08-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110814134028/http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/environment/article3500975.ece |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Julian Borger, diplomatic editor |url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2008/feb/26/food.unitednations |title=Feed the world? We are fighting a losing battle, UN admits |work=The Guardian |location=UK |accessdate=2011-11-30 |date=2008-02-26 |archive-date=2016-12-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161225150554/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2008/feb/26/food.unitednations |dead-url=no }}</ref>由Ug99秆锈病引起的小麦流行病在非洲和亚洲肆虐，引发广泛忧虑。恶性农作物疾病会在世界上大量毁坏小麦，使数以万计的人无法果腹。该疾病已经从非洲传入伊朗、阿富汗和巴基斯坦等地。<ref>{{cite news |author1=Robin McKie |author2=Xan Rice |url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2007/apr/22/food.foodanddrink |title=Millions face famine as crop disease rages |work=The Guardian |location=UK |accessdate=2011-11-30 |date=2007-04-22 |archive-date=2012-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121112125705/http://www.guardian.co.uk/science/2007/apr/22/food.foodanddrink |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name = NewSci>{{cite journal
 |url          = http://environment.newscientist.com/channel/earth/mg19425983.700-billions-at-risk-from-wheat-superblight.html
 |journal      = New Scientist Magazine
 |title        = Billions at risk from wheat super-blight
 |date         = 2007-04-03
 |accessdate   = 2007-04-19
 |issue        = 2598
 |pages        = 6–7
 |archive-date = 2007-05-09
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20070509024241/http://environment.newscientist.com/channel/earth/mg19425983.700-billions-at-risk-from-wheat-superblight.html
 |dead-url     = no
}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/IRIN/8112190676ab183b80e80199f821ef93.htm |title=IRAN: Killer fungus threatens wheat production in western areas |publisher=Alertnet.org |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2009-09-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090918081324/http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/IRIN/8112190676ab183b80e80199f821ef93.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>

若资源消耗殆尽，[[粮食安全|粮食安全]]就难以保障。有枯竭危险的资源包括石油、磷、粮食、鱼和水。<ref>{{cite web|title='Peak Oil' and the German Government: Military Study Warns of a Potentially Drastic Oil Crisis|url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/0,1518,715138,00.html|website=http://www.spiegel.de|accessdate=2017-04-22|archive-date=2012-05-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120518011920/http://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/0,1518,715138,00.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>"[https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2013/jul/06/food-supply-threat-water-wells-dry-up Global threat to food supply as water wells dry up, warns top environment expert] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2013/jul/06/food-supply-threat-water-wells-dry-up |date=20161208111640 }}". ''The Guardian''. 6 July 2013.</ref>2009年，不列颠科学家约翰·贝丁顿爵士预测2030年能源、食物和水需要增加50%以满足需求。<ref>"[https://www.theguardian.com/science/2009/mar/18/perfect-storm-john-beddington-energy-food-climate World faces 'perfect storm' of problems by 2030, chief scientist to warn] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2009/mar/18/perfect-storm-john-beddington-energy-food-climate |date=20161114162004 }}". The Guardian. 18 March 2009.</ref><ref>"[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/7951838.stm Global crisis 'to strike by 2030'] {{Wayback|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/7951838.stm |date=20161115024509 }}". BBC News. 19 March 2009.</ref>据联合国粮食及农业组织预测，2050年食物供应需要增加七成才能满足需求。<ref>"[http://www.finfacts.ie/irishfinancenews/article_1017966.shtml Global food production will have to increase 70% for additional 2.3 billion people by 2050] {{Wayback|url=http://www.finfacts.ie/irishfinancenews/article_1017966.shtml |date=20160310205117 }}". Finfacts.com. 24 September 2009.</ref>

====非洲====
''美国人口资料局''报道称非洲撒哈拉以南地区不但是该大陆最贫穷的地区，而且人口比世界其它地方增长得都快，“人口暴增令经济难以创造足够的工作来帮助人民摆脱贫困。”撒哈拉以南非洲10个国家中的7个出生率很高，但在联合国人类发展指数上垫底。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/africaandindianocean/10305000/Africas-population-to-double-to-2.4-billion-by-2050.html |title=Africa's population to double to 2.4 billion by 2050 |publisher=The Telegrapth |date=2013-09-12 |accessdate=2017-02-20 |archive-date=2020-11-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128095935/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/africaandindianocean/10305000/Africas-population-to-double-to-2.4-billion-by-2050.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

据[[联合国粮食及农业组织|联合国粮食及农业组织]]报告，每年有600万儿童因[[饥饿|饥饿]]和[[营养不良|营养不良]]离开，相比二十世纪九十年代，更多在撒哈拉以南的非洲人在这十年间营养不良。据《世界粮食危机状况》报告，在上述地区，10年前营养不良的人口有1亿7040万，而2000至2002年增至2亿350万。2001年，当地46.4%的人为极度赤贫。<ref>"[http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/politics/birth-rates-must-be-curbed-to-win-war-on-global-poverty-434387.html Birth rates 'must be curbed to win war on global poverty'] {{Wayback|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/politics/birth-rates-must-be-curbed-to-win-war-on-global-poverty-434387.html |date=20161227042142 }}". The Independent. 31 January 2007.</ref>

[[File:Dhaka_street_crowds.jpg|thumb]][[达卡|达卡]]街头人群]]

====人口与食物来源====
来自不同领域和政治背景的思想家，包括农业学家大卫·皮门特尔<ref name = "Hopfenberg and Pimentel">Hopfenberg, Russell and Pimentel, David, "Human Population Numbers as a Function of Food Supply", ''Environment, Development and Sustainability'', vol. 3, no. 1, March 2001, pp. 1–15</ref>、行为学家罗素·霍冯伯格<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Hopfenberg | first1 = R. | title = Human Carrying Capacity is Determined by Food Availability | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_population-and-environment_2003-11_25_2/page/109 | doi = 10.1023/B:POEN.0000015560.69479.c1 | journal = Population and Environment | volume = 25 | issue = 2 | pages = 109–117 | year = 2003 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref>、右翼人类学家弗吉尼亚·阿伯内西、<ref>Abernathy, Virginia, ''Population Politics'' ISBN 0-7658-0603-7</ref>生态学家[[加勒特·哈丁|加勒特·哈丁]]<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Hardin | first1 = Garrett | year = 1974 | title = [[Lifeboat_ethics|Lifeboat Ethics: the Case Against Helping the Poor]] | url = | journal = Psychology Today | volume = 8 | issue = | pages = 38–43}}</ref>、生态和人类学家彼得·法尔布、记者理查德·曼宁、<ref>{{cite interview |last=Manning |first=Richard |subjectlink=Richard Manning |interviewer=Sally Erickson and Timothy Scott Bennett |title=Richard Manning on the Green Revolution and the End of Cheap Oil |date=7 Sep 2011 |work=YouTube |accessdate=15 Oct 2013 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SbUnGIxbvTM |archive-date=2021-02-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210202100708/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SbUnGIxbvTM |dead-url=no }}</ref>环境生物学家艾伦·D·桑希尔、<ref>''Food Production & Population Growth'', video with Daniel Quinn and Alan Thornhill</ref>文化评论家、作家丹尼尔·奎恩、<ref>Quinn, Daniel, ''[[Ishmael_(novel)|Ishmael]]'' Bantam/Turner, 1995, ISBN 0613080939</ref>和无政府原始主义者约翰·哲忍<ref>{{cite speech|title=On Modernity and the Technosphere|first=John|last=Zerzan|location=Binghamton University|date=April 2, 2008|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3I9QJVNas5k|at=See 38:35 to 39:00.|access-date=2017-04-21|archive-date=2020-11-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201121133642/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3I9QJVNas5k|dead-url=no}}</ref>，认为人类人口和其它动物族群一样，当食物充足时扩张，稀缺时缩减。

这一理论的支持者辩护道每次食物产量增加，人口就增加。历史上人口情况大多证实这一理论，现在也如此。[[狩猎采集|狩猎采集]]时期人口随食物多少增减。在[[新石器革命|新石器革命]]后世界人口开始增加，食物供应也增加。这样，在[[绿色革命|绿色革命]]之后人口增速更快，并持续至今。通常，富裕国家会将多余食物支援穷国；不过，该理论支持者认为这事看似不错，但在长远会造成伤害。例如，彼得·法尔布称该悖论“人越多生产越多，催生人口进一步膨胀。”<ref>Farb, Peter: 1978, ''Humankind''. Boston, Houghton Mifflin.</ref>丹尼尔·奎恩也注意到这一现象，他称之为“食物竞赛”（类似[[核军备竞赛|核军备竞赛]]）。

批评者指出，现代发达国家食物最充足，出生率反而最低。事实上，一些发达国家人口不增反降。联合国预期有51个国家和地区，包括德国、意大利、日本和前苏联加盟国家，在2050年人口会比2005年的低。<ref>{{Cite book|url=http://www.un.org/esa/population/publications/WPP2004/WPP2004_Vol3_Final/WPP2004_Analytical_Report.pdf|title=''World Population Prospects The 2004 Revision, Volume III, Analytical Report''|last=|first=|date=2006年11月17日|publisher=聯合國經濟和社會事務部|accessdate=2017-08-09|isbn=978-9211514094|location=紐約|pages=xix|language=en|format=PDF|archive-date=2013-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111230031/http://www.un.org/esa/population/publications/WPP2004/WPP2004_Vol3_Final/WPP2004_Analytical_Report.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>这显示，将人口对比某一政治区域考量，并不总是符合食物供应的变化。然而，全球人口作为整体依然根据食物供给总量变化，许多富裕国家是穷人的主要食物“出口方”，这样，“将食物从富裕地区出口到不足地区（Allaby, 1984; Pimentel et al., 1999），使得食物不足地区的人口进一步增加。”<ref name = "Hopfenberg and Pimentel"/>

无论对人口与食物来源之间的关系功能如何批评，人口从全局来看增长无疑，<ref>[[Daniel_Quinn|Daniel Quinn]] (1996). ''[[The_Story_of_B|The Story of B]]'', pp. 304–305, Random House Publishing Group, ISBN 0553379011.</ref>伴随的是食物总量净增长。当农业发展时，这一现象持续了约一万年。富裕国家人口减少不能将理论全盘否定，因为世界是个全球系统，食物可以越过国界送往稀缺地区。霍冯伯格和皮门特尔的发现支持双方观点，<ref name = "Hopfenberg and Pimentel"/>奎恩直接批评道“第一世界的农民在第三世界的人口爆炸火上浇油。”<ref>Quinn, Daniel: "The Question (ID Number 122)", Retrieved October 2014 from {{cite web |url=http://www.ishmael.org/Interaction/QandA/Detail.CFM?Record%3D122 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-10-18 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304064622/http://ishmael.org/interaction/qanda/detail.cfm?record=122 |archivedate=2016-03-04 }}.</ref>另外，假说不能因某一案例简单推翻，如德国近期人口趋势；很明显，其它因素限制了富裕国家人口：避孕、教育、社会规则等，更重要的是国与国之间经济现实的差异。

====缺水恶果====
缺水已经迫使众多小国大幅进口粮食，若非应用技术，中国和印度等大国也会如此。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.atimes.com/atimes/South_Asia/HG21Df01.html |title=Asia Times Online :: South Asia news – India grows a grain crisis |publisher=Atimes.com |date=2006-07-21 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2018-02-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180221083541/http://www.atimes.com/atimes/South_Asia/HG21Df01.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>由于大幅度透支可持续性，一些国家用水评分不佳（包括中国北方、美国和印度）。{{Citation needed|date=April 2010}}其它受影响的国家包括巴基斯坦、伊朗和墨西哥。透支已经导致用水紧张，使得粮食歉收。虽然对含水层再三压榨，中国粮食还是因此歉收。这使得粮价上涨。本世纪中叶，约30亿人将会出生在缺水国家里。[[海水淡化|海水淡化]]被认为是解决缺水行之有效的方法。<ref name="ejpress-water">{{cite web |url=http://www.ejpress.org/article/4873 |title=EJP | News | France | French-run water plant launched in Israel |publisher=Ejpress.org |date=2005-12-28 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091213050101/http://www.ejpress.org/article/4873 |archivedate=2009-12-13 }}</ref><ref name="edie-distinct">{{cite web |url=http://www.edie.net/news/news_story.asp?id=11402&channel=0 |title=Black & Veatch-Designed Desalination Plant Wins Global Water Distinction |publisher=Edie.net |date=2006-05-04 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100324144203/http://www.edie.net/news/news_story.asp?id=11402&channel=0 |archivedate=2010-03-24 }}</ref>

在中国和印度之后，又有一些较小的国家大幅度缺水：阿尔及利亚、埃及、伊朗、墨西哥和巴基斯坦。其中四个已经大幅度进口粮食。只有巴基斯坦自给自足。但随着人口每年增加400万，巴基斯坦会很快跑到世界市场上去买粮。<ref name="The Food Bubble Economy"/>

===土地===
[[File:Landusepiechart.png|thumb]]

世界资源学会称：“耕地和牧地的农业转型已经影响了33亿公顷，约占土地的26%。总而言之，农业取代了温带和热带森林的三分之一以及自然草地的四分之一。”<ref>{{cite web |url=http://earthtrends.wri.org/features/view_feature.php?theme=8&fid=34 |title=Domesticating the World: Conversion of Natural Ecosystems |publisher=World Resources Institute |date=September 2000 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070219144823/http://earthtrends.wri.org/features/view_feature.php?fid=34&theme=8 |archivedate=2007-02-19 |accessdate=2017-04-23 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://earthtrends.wri.org/features/view_feature.php?theme=9&fid=8 |title=Grasslands in Pieces: Modification and Conversion Take a Toll |publisher=World Resources Institute |date=December 2000 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070219145245/http://earthtrends.wri.org/features/view_feature.php?fid=8&theme=9 |archivedate=2007-02-19 |accessdate=2017-04-23 }}</ref>土地的四成正在转型或支离破碎；不足四分之一是处女地，主要在极地和沙漠。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.globio.info/impacts/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070630131304/http://www.globio.info/impacts/ |archivedate=2007-06-30 |title=GLOBIO, an initiative of the United Nations Environment Programme (Archive) |publisher=Web.archive.org |date=2007-06-30 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |dead-url=no }}</ref>由于[[土壤盐化|盐碱化]]、森林砍伐、[[沙漠化|沙漠化]]、[[侵蚀作用|土壤侵蚀]]、和[[城市蔓延|城市蔓延]]，土壤变得不再好用。[[全球变暖|全球变暖]]也导致许多富饶耕地被淹。<ref>John Houghton, ''Global Warming: The Complete Briefing'', Cambridge University Press, 2009 ISBN 978-0-521-70916-3</ref>能源发展也会大量占用土地，如建[[水力发电|水电大坝]]。因此，可用土地是有限因素。据估算，可用土地只要有一半已经用于耕作，而对现存保留地大大高估令人不安。<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Young | first1 = A. | journal = Environment, Development and Sustainability | volume = 1 |title=Is there Really Spare Land? A Critique of Estimates of Available Cultivable Land in Developing Countries| pages = 3–2 | doi = 10.1023/A:1010055012699 | year = 1999 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref>

新型选择性繁殖和[[杂交种|杂交]]植物可食用部分（果实、蔬菜和粮食）更多，不可食用部分更小。然而，这些农业技术成就已经作古，新成就高不可攀。新技术使得农作物可以在某些边际土地生长。[[水产养殖|水产养殖]]理论上可以增加可用土地。[[水耕栽培|水耕栽培]]和真菌作物让食物增产，即便这可能是精耕细作，但不需花费大量土地或依赖气候阳光。另一些人认为开垦所有土地未必增产，因为一些边际土地只能用[[刀耕火耨|刀耕火耨]]这种不可持续方式来耕作。即便有了现代农业技术，可持续生产依然存疑。

一些国家，如阿拉伯联合酋长国，特别是其[[杜拜|迪拜]]酋长国和荷兰一样，通过[[填海|填海造陆]]建造了大量人工岛、大坝和堤坝来增加国土面积。<ref>{{cite news|last=Tagliabue|first=John|title=The Dutch seek to claim more land from the sea|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/07/world/europe/07iht-journal.1.17618884.html|accessdate=2017-02-09|work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]|date=2008-11-07|archive-date=2020-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129014534/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/07/world/europe/07iht-journal.1.17618884.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Shepard|first=Wade|title="The gift from the sea": through land reclamation, China keeps growing and growing|url=http://www.citymetric.com/skylines/gift-sea-through-land-reclamation-china-keeps-growing-and-growing-1350|accessdate=2017-02-09|work=CityMetric|publisher=[[New_Statesman|New Statesman]]|date=2015-08-25|archive-date=2020-08-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200810162442/https://www.citymetric.com/skylines/gift-sea-through-land-reclamation-china-keeps-growing-and-growing-1350|dead-url=no}}</ref>一些科学家称在未来，人口稠密城市会在摩天大厦内用[[垂直农法|垂直农法]]耕作。<ref name = "BBC-nyc">{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/6752795.stm | work=BBC News | title=Vertical farming in the big Apple | date=2007-06-19 | accessdate=2010-05-20 | first=Jeremy | last=Cooke | archive-date=2021-01-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109021031/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/6752795.stm | dead-url=no }}</ref>质疑者耻笑地球空间有限的说法，认为65亿人可以舒服地塞进美国德克萨斯州大小的地区（约{{convert|269000|sqmi|km2|2|disp=or|sigfig=6}}）。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://overpopulationisamyth.com/overpopulation-the-making-of-a-myth#FAQ5|title=Overpopulation: The Making of a Myth|accessdate=2010-02-13|archive-date=2017-07-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170711020525/https://overpopulationisamyth.com/overpopulation-the-making-of-a-myth#FAQ5|dead-url=no}}</ref>然而，人类影响的不简简单单是居住面积。

===化石燃料===
{{See also|哈伯特顶点}}
[[File:Hubbert_peak_oil_plot.svg|left]]

对人口乐观主义的批评指出该观点忽视石油及其它[[化石燃料|化石燃料]]的枯竭，让[[肥料|肥料]]和交通燃料难以生产。<ref>"[http://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/world-oil-supplies-are-set-to-run-out-faster-than-expected-warn-scientists-6262621.html World oil supplies are set to run out faster than expected, warn scientists] {{Wayback|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/world-oil-supplies-are-set-to-run-out-faster-than-expected-warn-scientists-6262621.html |date=20160908194714 }}". ''The Independent''. 14 June 2007.</ref>1992年，[[阿尔·戈尔|阿尔·戈尔]]在《濒临失衡的地球》写道：“... 建立全球协作计划来完全消除内燃机的战略计划是可能的，或许要用二十五年... ”<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.crossroad.to/articles2/Gore.html |title=Al Gore's Vision of Global Salvation |publisher=Crossroad.to |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2021-01-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125142045/http://www.crossroad.to/articles2/Gore.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>美国生产的一半左右的石油被提炼成为汽油，用于内燃机。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tonto.eia.doe.gov/energyexplained/index.cfm?page=gasoline_home |title=Gasoline – Energy Explained, Your Guide To Understanding Energy |publisher=Tonto.eia.doe.gov |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101104053716/http://tonto.eia.doe.gov/energyexplained/index.cfm?page=gasoline_home |archive-date=2010-11-04 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

应[[美国能源部|美国能源部]]要求，报告《世界石油生产顶峰：影响、缓解和风险管理》于2005年2月出版、2007年修正更新，常被称为赫希报告。<ref name="hirsch_report">{{cite web
 |url          = http://www.netl.doe.gov/publications/others/pdf/Oil_Peaking_NETL.pdf
 |title        = Peaking Of World Oil Production: Impacts, Mitigation, & Risk Management
 |first        = Robert L.
 |last         = Hirsch
 |first2       = Roger
 |last2        = Bezdek
 |first3       = Robert
 |last3        = Wendling
 |date         = February 2005
 |publisher    = Science Applications International Corporation/U.S.Department of Energy, National Energy Technology Laboratory
 |format       = PDF
 |accessdate   = 2009-11-28
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20091215043338/http://www.netl.doe.gov/publications/others/pdf/Oil_Peaking_NETL.pdf
 |archive-date = 2009-12-15
 |dead-url     = yes
}}</ref><ref>{{cite web
 |url          = http://netl.doe.gov/File%20Library/Research/Energy%20Analysis/Publications/DOE-NETL-2007-1263-PeakingWorldOilProd-RecentForecasts.pdf
 |title        = Peaking of World Oil Production: Recent Forecasts
 |first        = Robert L.
 |last         = Hirsch
 |date         = February 2007
 |publisher    = Science Applications International Corporation/U.S.Department of Energy, National Energy Technology Laboratory
 |format       = PDF
 |accessdate   = 2015-02-19
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20170201083330/http://netl.doe.gov/File%20Library/Research/Energy%20Analysis/Publications/DOE-NETL-2007-1263-PeakingWorldOilProd-RecentForecasts.pdf
 |archive-date = 2017-02-01
 |dead-url     = yes
}}</ref>
该书研究了[[哈伯特顶点|油峰]]出现的时间框架，必要的缓和措施以及沿时间轴可能出现的影响。报告总结称世界石油顶峰将会出现，甚至可能会很突然。在顶峰出现前20年准备缓和措施可以躲过危机。

乐观主义者反驳称在合适的可替代技术发展应用前，如核能或各种[[可再生能源|可再生能源]]等，化石燃料足以应付。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://economics.about.com/cs/macroeconomics/a/run_out_of_oil.htm |title=We Will Never Run Out of Oil |publisher=Economics.about.com |date=2011-06-27 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2017-01-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170117132623/http://economics.about.com/cs/macroeconomics/a/run_out_of_oil.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>通过热解聚来处理垃圾、污水和农业废物来生产肥料的方式已经出现。<ref>{{cite web |last=Lemley |first=Brad |url=http://discovermagazine.com/2003/may/featoil/ |title=Anything Into Oil | Alternative Energy |publisher=DISCOVER Magazine |date=2003-05-01 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2019-11-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191118192449/http://discovermagazine.com/2003/may/featoil |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Lemley |first=Brad |url=http://discovermagazine.com/2006/apr/anything-oil/ |title=Anything Into Oil | Alternative Energy |publisher=DISCOVER Magazine |date=2006-04-02 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2019-11-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191120061257/http://discovermagazine.com/2006/apr/anything-oil |dead-url=no }}</ref>

===貧富===
[[File:Percentage_living_on_less_than_$1_per_day_1981-2001.png|thumb]]

联合国指出约8.5亿人营养不良或饥饿难耐，<ref name="FAO-Italy">Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (2001). [http://www.fao.org/docrep/003/y1500e/y1500e00.htm Food Insecurity: When People Live With Hunger and Fear Starvation. The State of Food insecurity in the World 2001] {{Wayback|url=http://www.fao.org/docrep/003/y1500e/y1500e00.htm|date=20161201161538}}. FAO, ISBN 92-5-104628-X</ref>有11亿人喝不到安全的饮用水。<ref name = "Shiklomanov-11-32">{{Cite journal | last1 = Shiklomanov | first1 = I. A. | doi = 10.1080/02508060008686794 | title = Appraisal and Assessment of World Water Resources | journal = Water International | volume = 25 | pages = 11–32 | year = 2000 | pmid =  | pmc = }}</ref>从1980年算起，世界经济增长380%，但生活在每天不足5美元的人数增至11多亿。<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/global-development-professionals-network/2015/sep/23/developing-poor-countries-de-develop-rich-countries-sdgs Forget 'developing' poor countries, it's time to 'de-develop' rich countries] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theguardian.com/global-development-professionals-network/2015/sep/23/developing-poor-countries-de-develop-rich-countries-sdgs |date=20161201174824 }}. ''[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]].'' September 23, 2015.</ref>

1997年，联合国《人类发展报告》称：“在过去15至20年间，超过100多个发展中国家和一些东欧国家在发展上遭受灾难性失误。在工业化国家中，生活质量下降之深之久除了三十年代大萧条外没有可比的。这导致10亿人收入跌回10年前、20年前甚至30年前的水平”。类似地，虽然非洲撒哈拉以南“饥民”比率有所下降，但绝对人数却随总人数的增长而增长。比率从1970年的38%跌至1996年的33%，预期2010年会跌至30%。<ref name=autogenerated1 />但该地区人口在1970至1996年几乎翻倍。要让饥民人数保持不变，比率必须拦腰减半。<ref name = "ecosystems-#3"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.greenfacts.org/en/ecosystems/millennium-assessment-3/3-human-wellbeing-poverty.htm#3p0 |title=3. How have ecosystem changes affected human well-being and poverty alleviation? |publisher=Greenfacts.org |date=2011-10-17 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2020-11-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201106122614/https://www.greenfacts.org/en/ecosystems/millennium-assessment-3/3-human-wellbeing-poverty.htm#3p0 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[File:TFR_vs_PPP_2015.png|thumb]]对比各国[[各国人均国内生产总值列表_(购买力平价)|人均GDP（PPP）]]，2015年<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/fields/2127.html|title=Field Listing: Total Fertility Rate|website=[[The_World_Factbook|The World Factbook]]|accessdate=2016-04-24|archive-date=2013-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130811191145/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/fields/2127.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>
<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/resources/the-world-factbook/rankorder/2004rank.html|title=Country Comparison: GDP – Per Capita (PPP)|website=[[The_World_Factbook|The World Factbook]]|accessdate=2016-04-24|archive-date=2020-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201116092828/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/resources/the-world-factbook/rankorder/2004rank.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>]]

若妇女收入增加、束缚越少，子女数量会减少（如从6人减至2人）、质量则会上升。<ref>{{cite video|people=Brand, Stewart|title=Lecture Series presented by KPMG – Whole Earth Discipline|url=http://www.q2cfestival.com/play.php?lecture_id=8030|date=2009-10-24|publisher=Perimeter Institute, Quantum to Cosmos (Q2C) Festival|location=Waterloo, Ontario, Canada|accessdate=2009-10-25|time=50:30|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100128231537/http://www.q2cfestival.com/play.php?lecture_id=8030|archivedate=2010-01-28}}</ref>

两者关系并非简单的因果关系，其中掺杂着复杂的生育率、死亡率和经济发展等因素。

生活环境破败也对人口造成非常恶劣的影响，如疟疾和艾滋病等疾病。缺少营养、脏乱差、缺医少药、死亡率高、出生率地会对人口造成打击。

==环境==
[[File:Traffic_jam_on_Phu_Nhuan_district.JPG|thumb]]堵车]]
{{cquote|你知道，当我们最初建立世界自然基金会时，是为了拯救濒危物种不至灭绝。但我们失败的一塌糊涂；一个都没救成。如果把钱全塞进避孕套里，或许能办得更好。<small>彼得·斯科特爵士，[[世界自然基金会|世界自然基金会]]创始人</small><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.cosmosmagazine.com/opinion/a-plague-people/|title=A plague of people|work=''[[Cosmos_(magazine)|Cosmos]]''|date=2010-05-13|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161106130856/http://archive.cosmosmagazine.com/opinion/a-plague-people/|archivedate=2016年11月6日}}</ref>
}}

不但如此，一些国家人口众多，环境问题严峻，单单控制人口增长并不一定在环境问题上一蹴而就。<ref name="UN World Population Report 2001">{{cite web|url=http://www.un.org/esa/population/publications/wpm/wpm2001.pdf|format=PDF|title=UN World Population Report 2001|page=31|accessdate=2008-12-16|archive-date=2018-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180211183328/http://www.un.org/esa/population/publications/wpm/wpm2001.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>不过，当人口众多的发展中国家进行工业化时，污染和能耗一定会增加。

世界观察研究所称2006年中国和印度经济繁荣是“改变全球生物圈的星际动力”。报告称：

{{quote|简而言之，世界的生态承载能力不能持续满足中国、印度、日本、欧洲和美国的野心以及其它世界的渴望。<ref>"[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/4604556.stm Booming nations 'threaten Earth'] {{Wayback|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/science/nature/4604556.stm |date=20200914130728 }}". BBC News (2006-01-12).</ref>}}

早在二十世纪初，人口过多就深刻影响地球环境了。<ref name="Nielsen" />据全球足迹网络：“今天人类使用的资源和排放的废物相当于1.5个地球。”<ref name="HO">Human overpopulation. Animal Welfare Institute. Retrieved 2014/10/25 from {{cite web |url=https://awionline.org/content/human-overpopulation |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-12-01 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022222110/http://awionline.org/content/human-overpopulation |archivedate=2016-10-22 }}</ref>[[生态系统服务|生态系统服务]]损耗导致的[[环境退化|环境退化]]会带来经济后果。<ref>Daily, Gretchen C. and Ellison, Katherine (2003) ''The New Economy of Nature: The Quest to Make Conservation Profitable'', Island Press ISBN 1559631546</ref>在科学证明环境伤害以外，一些人认为保护物种不至灭绝是道德责任。环保作家杰里米·里夫金称：“我们的人口累赘和城市化生活是以大型生态系统和生物栖息地为代价的... 当庆祝世界城市化时，我们迅速临近了另一个历史分水岭：荒野消失了。这并不意外。”<ref>{{cite news
 |url=http://www.thestar.com/opinion/article/164832
 |title=The risks of too much city in a crowded world
 |work=Toronto Star
 |date=2006-12-24
 |first=Jeremy
 |last=Rifkin
 |accessdate=2017-04-21
 |archive-date=2012-05-22
 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120522202317/http://www.thestar.com/opinion/article/164832
 |dead-url=no
 }}</ref>

[[美国科学促进会|美国科学促进会]]前主席彼得·雷文在《[https://web.archive.org/web/20110309092803/http://atlas.aaas.org/ AAAS 人口与环境图册]》中称：“我们在建立可持续发展世界上努力如何？显而易见，过去半个世纪是个创伤，人类数量、财富（人均消费）以及我们选择的技术造成叠加影响，以不可持续的高速度继续剥削着地球资源... 在很短的时间内，我们失去世界[[表土|表土]]的四分之一、耕地的五分之一、深深地改变了[[大气层|大气层]]的成分、破坏了大片森林和其它自然[[动物栖息地|动物栖息地]]，却没有补偿修复。最糟糕的是，我们以超过历史水平百倍的速度加快了生物[[绝灭|绝灭]]，永久地失去物种，在二十一世纪末威胁到所有主要物种的生存。”

据称，如果中国和印度也像美国人均资源那样消费，到2030年就得要整个地球来满足他们的需求。<ref>"[http://www.worldwatch.org/node/3893 State of the World 2006: China and India Hold World in Balance] {{Wayback|url=http://www.worldwatch.org/node/3893 |date=20160415082807 }}". [[Worldwatch_Institute|Worldwatch Institute]]. 11 January 2006.</ref>从长远角度来看，日益稀少的资源会影响冲突加增，<ref>"[http://www.globalissues.org/EnvIssues/Population/Result.asp Effects of Over-Consumption and Increasing Populations] {{Wayback|url=http://www.globalissues.org/EnvIssues/Population/Result.asp |date=20080608020547 }}". 26 September 2001. Retrieved 19 June 2007.</ref>最坏的结果是[[马尔萨斯灾难|马尔萨斯灾难]]。

许多研究将人口增长与[[温室气体|温室气体]]及[[气候变化|气候变化]]效应联系起来。<ref>[[John_T._Houghton|John T. Houghton]] (2004)."''[https://books.google.com/books?id=jE9mwoLXdwYC&pg=PA326&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false Global warming: the complete briefing] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jE9mwoLXdwYC&pg=PA326&dq&hl=en#v=onepage&q=&f=false|date=20200930192758}}''". [[Cambridge_University_Press|Cambridge University Press]]. p.326. ISBN 0-521-52874-7</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/environment/once-taboo-population-enters-climate-debate-1834789.html |title=Once taboo, population enters climate debate |work=The Independent |location=London |date=2009-12-05 |accessdate=2010-01-21 |archive-date=2015-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925032248/http://www.independent.co.uk/environment/once-taboo-population-enters-climate-debate-1834789.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==战乱==
{{cquote|各国人口过多已经成为人民健康的严重威胁，对在这个星球上任何组建和平的企图都造成了严重阻碍。<small>[[阿尔伯特·爱因斯坦|阿尔伯特·爱因斯坦]]</small><ref>{{cite web|title=Quotations|url=http://www.populationmatters.org/making-case/quotations/|website=http://www.populationmatters.org/|accessdate=2014-07-01}}</ref>
}}

有人认为<ref>{{cite book |last=Champion |first=Tony |editor1-first=Peter |editor1-last=Daniels |editor2-first=Michael |editor2-last=Bradshaw |editor3-first=Denis |editor3-last=Shaw |editor4-first=James |editor4-last=Sidaway  |title=An Introduction to Human Geography Issues for the 21st Century Second edition|url=https://archive.org/details/introductiontohu002edunse_n7b4 |publisher=Pearson Education |year=2005 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/introductiontohu002edunse_n7b4/page/88 88]–111 |chapter=Chapter 4: Demographic transformations |isbn=0-131-21766-6}}</ref>人口过多会导致国家内外紧张。现代词汇“[[生存空间|生存空间]]”支持这一观点，认为人口过多会导致资源稀缺，使得年轻人无法通过和平劳动方式找到机会而诱发战乱。

=== 對假說的評論 ===
由於經驗與觀察的根據，主張人口壓力會導致戰亂增加的假說近年來受到批評。兩項針對具體歷史社會與跨文化分析的研究都無法找出人口密度及戰爭發生率間的正相關關係。

==建议==
{{cquote|这个文化对人类和自然世界暴力相向，就目前的暴力水平而言提及减少人口和消费不能不谈到暴力和贫困，这并不是说削减它们必须使用暴力，而是暴力和贫困已经被我们的文化默认。<small>《残局》，德里克· 延森著，2006年</small><ref>{{cite book |last=Jensen|first=Derrick |date=2006 |title=Endgame, Vol. 1: The Problem of Civilization|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CSsfg3325iEC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA129#v=onepage&q&f=false|location= |publisher=[[Seven_Stories_Press|Seven Stories Press]]|page=129 |isbn=978-1583227305|author-link=Derrick Jensen}}</ref>
}}

一些方法和缓和措施被用来对付人口过多问题。一些方法被用在全球层面上（如联合国举措），另一些则用在地方、省市和其它组织层面，还有一些则用在家庭和个人层面。有的缓和措施旨在设立社会规范。人口过多威胁环境，因此社会必须对目前的社会规范做出改变来逆转一些环境问题。

例如，中国政府采取政策控制夫妻生育人数。建立市场策略来教育公众有关人口过多的恶果。“干预可以低成本普及。各种印刷资料（传单、手册、说明和贴纸）得在社区分发，如敬拜场所、运动会、当地菜市场、学校和停车场（的士/公交站）等。”<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.community.peacecorpsconnect.org/view/514/utilizing-social-marking-and-social-norms-to-addresss-problems-in-the-gambia |title=Utilizing social marketing and social norms to address problems in gambia |date=2009-08-13 |accessdate=2010-12-12 }}{{dead link|date=2017年11月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

一些宣传工作介绍了问题，让社会规则能够更容易改变。某些政府政策让社会更容易接受避孕和堕胎举措。与全球扼制人口过多相反的例子是阿富汗，“阿富汗总统哈米德·卡尔扎伊在2009年3月颁布的什叶派个人身份法力挫阿富汗什叶派妇女权益和自由。根据该法，除非生病，妇女无权拒绝丈夫性行为，否则可以不许吃饭。”<ref>{{cite news
 |url=http://www.overpopulation.org/
 |title=Put women's rights back on the afghan
 |publisher=Daily News Egypt
 |date=2010-08-27
 |accessdate=2010-12-12
 |archive-date=2010-08-22
 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100822190434/http://www.overpopulation.org/
 |dead-url=no
 }}</ref>

===教育与授权===
一个选择是重视对人口过多的教育、计划生育和[[生育控制|生育控制]]，包括使用简易有效的男性和[[女性避孕套|女性]][[避孕套|避孕套]]、避孕药和[[子宫环|子宫环]]等。全世界近四成怀孕是意外（每年近8000万）。<ref>"[https://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5gevGOq7Vctd1FmJkzO3gapTqX4ZA Population growth driving climate change, poverty: experts] {{Wayback|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5gevGOq7Vctd1FmJkzO3gapTqX4ZA |date=20120523114015 }}". [[Agence_France-Presse|Agence France-Presse]] (2009-09-21).</ref>世界最贫困地区约有3亿5000万妇女不想要最小的孩子、不想多要孩子或想隔一段时间再要孩子，但缺乏信息和可行方式及服务来规划家庭大小。2001年，美国约有近一半怀孕是意外。<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1363/3809006|title=Disparities in Rates of Unintended Pregnancy In the United States, 1994 and 2001|author1=Finer, Lawrence B.  |author2=Henshaw, Stanley K. |journal=Perspectives on Sexual and Reproductive Health|volume =38|issue =2|pages =90–96|year=2006|pmid=16772190}}</ref>在发展中国家，每年约有514,000位妇女因怀孕或堕胎致死，<ref>"[https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20070816231834/http://www.unfpa.org/news/news.cfm?ID=85&Language=1 Netherlands Again Number One Donor to United Nations Population Fund]". United Nations Population Fund (UNFPA).</ref>其中死亡的86%出现在非洲撒哈拉以南和南亚。<ref>"[http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/releases/2007/pr56/en/index.html Maternal mortality ratio falling too slowly to meet goal] {{Wayback|url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/releases/2007/pr56/en/index.html |date=20131031223858 }}". [[WHO|WHO]] (2007-10-12).</ref>此外，近800万婴儿因营养不良、患小病、特别是饮用水不干净而死亡。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1571/is_46_17/ai_80774574 | work=Insight on the News | title=Q: should the United Nations support more family-planning services for poor countries? | first=Werner | last=Fornos | date=2001-12-10 | accessdate=2017-04-23 | archive-date=2012-07-08 | archive-url=https://archive.is/20120708011842/findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m1571/is_46_17/ai_80774574 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

辩论的核心焦点常在[[妇女权利|妇女权利]]和[[生育权|生育权]]上。<ref name=popsearch>{{cite web|title=Population Matters search on "reproductive rights"|url=http://populationmatters.org/search_results.php?q=%22reproductive+rights%22|website=populationmatters.org|publisher=Population Matters|accessdate=2017-04-23|archive-date=2020-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308204450/http://populationmatters.org/search_results.php?q=%22reproductive+rights%22|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

<blockquote>“我唯一看到的希望之光虽然不多，就是无论如何女人要把持自己的人生，包括政治和社会的；当医学设施能够让她们决定控制生育，丈夫允许她们做出决定，生育率就会下降。女人可不想生十二个死九个。” —— [[戴維·阿滕伯勒|大卫·阿滕伯勒爵士]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Sir David Attenborough on the roots of Climatic problems|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/sir-david-attenborough-this-awful-summer-weve-only-ourselves-to-blame-7942405.html|website=www.independent.co.uk|publisher=The Independent, UK broadsheet newspaper|accessdate=2017-04-15|archive-date=2020-08-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801045748/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/sir-david-attenborough-this-awful-summer-weve-only-ourselves-to-blame-7942405.html|dead-url=no}}</ref></blockquote>

2008年6月，埃及卫生和人口部长哈特姆·贾巴利宣布政府通过教育和妇女劳动来减少人口的计划，并为此出资4亿8000万埃及镑（约合9000万美元）。<ref>{{cite web|author=Independent Newspapers Online |url=http://www.iol.co.za/index.php?from=rss_Africa&set_id=1&click_id=68&art_id=nw20080611085517622C989460 |title=Population woes weigh down Egypt |publisher=IOL |date=2008-06-11 |accessdate=2011-11-30}}</ref>

商界大亨[[泰德·透纳|泰德·透纳]]提出“自愿、非强制性”的独生子女计划。英国相关人口组织[[Population_Matters|Population Matters]]举办了“二胎或更少”的运动，呼吁人们为小型家庭努力。

===管控===
[[File:Growthbydevelopedvslessdeveloped.jpg|thumb]]

人口过多问题可以通过[[生育控制|生育控制]]缓解，一些国家，如中华人民共和国，采取了严格措施控制出生率。反对生育控制的宗教和意识形态常被认为是导致人口过多和贫困的因素。<ref>{{cite news
 |url         = http://news.independent.co.uk/world/politics/article2201090.ece
 |title       = Birth rates 'must be curbed to win war on global poverty'
 |work        = The Independent
 |location    = London
 |date        = 2007-01-31
 |accessdate  = 2010-05-20
 |deadurl     = yes
 |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20080119183753/http://news.independent.co.uk/world/politics/article2201090.ece
 |archivedate = 2008年1月19日
}}</ref>

2014年，联合国预测世界人口在2100年增至96至123亿有八成可能性。新增人口大多数出现在非洲和南亚。非洲人口预期会从目前的10亿增至2100年的30到40亿，亚洲会在同期再增10亿人。<ref>Kunzig, Robert, "A world with 11 billion people? New population projections shatter earlier estimates." National Geographic, September 18, 2014, {{cite web |url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2014/09/140918-population-global-united-nations-2100-boom-africa/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-02-25 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161219061416/http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2014/09/140918-population-global-united-nations-2100-boom-africa/ |archivedate=2016-12-19 }}</ref>由于非洲中值年龄很低（如乌干达为15岁），若要立刻达到发达国家标准，生育信用得限制到每两位妇女生育一位宝宝。一些国家人口金字塔底座很大，对于那些到了生育年龄的人来说，得再等一代人才行。<ref name="Arth, Michael E. 2010, pp. 352-362"/>一个人口增长态势的例子是中国，在采取独生子女政策后，又生了约400,000多人。亚瑟认为焦点应放在发达国家，他们给予的生育信用和额外补贴能够让发展中国家人口增长归零并迅速提升生活质量。<ref name="Arth, Michael E. 2010, pp. 352-362"/>

印度前总理[[英迪拉·甘地|英迪拉·甘地]]的儿子[[桑贾伊·甘地|桑贾伊·甘地]]在1975至1977年间推行了[[强制绝育|强制绝育]]政策。根据官方要求，有两位或两位孩子以上的男士都要申请绝育，但绝育更多的是妇女而非男士。据信，一些未婚青年男士、政治对手和愚民也被绝育{{Citation needed | reason=Claims neither supported nor mentioned by given source | date=October 2016}}。这项政策依然记忆犹新，备受批评，使得公众反感[[计划生育|计划生育]]，数十年来阻碍政府计划。<ref>Vinay Lal. [http://www.sscnet.ucla.edu/southasia/History/Independent/Indira.html Indira Gandhi] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sscnet.ucla.edu/southasia/History/Independent/Indira.html |date=20160729163515 }}, UCLA College of Letters and Science</ref>

城市设计师[[米高·亚瑟|米高·亚瑟]]给出的建议是“可选的、市场化的生育证书计划”，即“生育信用”。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.corrupt.org/act/interviews/michael_e_arth/ |title=Interview: City Architect and Reconstructor Michael E. Arth by Alex Birch |publisher=Corrupt.org |date=2008-05-22 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090105083809/http://www.corrupt.org/act/interviews/michael_e_arth |archivedate=2009年1月5日 }}</ref>生育信用不会限制妇女生育数量，若所生子女数量超过人口零增长指标的话，就得购买证书。例如，第一位孩子免费，市场则会决定多出生孩子所需缴纳的金额。多余的信用额度过期作废，以免被投机炒作。实际信用费用只是养育儿童成长费用的一部分，以便告知妇女不要不加思索就要孩子，为自己和社会带来长期后果。<ref name="Arth, Michael E. 2010, pp. 352-362">Arth, Michael E., ''Democracy and the Common Wealth: Breaking the Stranglehold of the Special Interests'', Golden Apples Media, 2010, Chapter 35: "Overpopulation" pp. 352–362</ref>

类似亚瑟生育信用的另一项举措是国家财政补贴，对自愿[[绝育|绝育]]者予以经济、物质、服务等补助。印度政府曾经使用这项政策。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-south-asia-13982031 |title=Goods for sterilization |accessdate=2017-04-21 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304083235/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-south-asia-13982031 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

===城市化===
虽然城市人口密度不断增加（出现巨型城市），[[联合国人居署|联合国人居署]]在报告中称城市化可能是全球人口增长最佳缓和办法。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/in_depth/6244496.stm |title=UN Habitat calling urban living 'a good thing |publisher=BBC News |date=2007-06-27 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2020-08-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801200918/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/in_depth/6244496.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>城市将人类活动汇集在有限区域，限制了自然破坏。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.michellenijhuis.com/ |title=National Geographic Magazine; Special report 2008: Changing Climate (Village Green-article by Michelle Nijhuis) |publisher=Michellenijhuis.com |date=2011-09-29 |accessdate=2011-11-30 |archive-date=2021-01-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210127231838/https://michellenijhuis.com/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>但这种缓和效果只有在[[城市规划|城市规划]]大幅改进，服务合理维持时才能显现<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unhabitat.org/content.asp?cid=2523&catid=5&typeid=6&subMenuId=0 |title=UN Habitat calling to rethink urban planning |publisher=Unhabitat.org |accessdate=2011-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110807191706/http://www.unhabitat.org/content.asp?cid=2523&catid=5&typeid=6&subMenuId=0 |archivedate=2011-08-07 }}</ref>。

===移除多餘人口===
{{main|优生学|优等种族}}
透過移除多餘的人口，如[[自殺|自殺]]、[[殺人|殺人]]、[[人類自願滅絕運動|人類自願滅絕運動]]、[[計劃生育|計劃生育]]、[[絕育|絕育]]、[[自宮|自宮]]、甚至發動[[戰爭|戰爭]]等等，可以舒緩世界人口過剩問題。此外，利用[[物競天擇|物競天擇]]的原理，篩選出條件較差（如[[體質|體質]]、[[智商|智商]]、[[性格|性格]]、[[能力|能力]]、[[種姓|種姓]]、[[血統|血統]]、[[種族|種族]]甚至隨機篩選等都能納入考慮之列）的人口並將之移除亦能有效舒緩人口過剩。[[達爾文獎|達爾文獎]]的存在鼓勵那些自願將自身移除於基因庫之外的人。

===太空移民===
{{main|太空移民}}
自從人類開始對宇宙的探索之後，太空移民就一直是人類的夢想。但到目前為止，還沒有任何一個太空殖民地被建立起來。況且在太空建立殖民地要面對一系列巨大的技術和經濟挑戰。部份支持太空移民的人認為，此舉能減輕人口過剩的負面影響。如果控制了太空資源，建立地外生物棲息地，地球將不再有增長的限制。雖然地球的許多資源是不可再生的，但是地外殖民地可以滿足地球上大部分的資源需求。隨着對太空資源的取用，對地球資源的需求將下降。

